<TITLE>Chemdrug features</TITLE>
<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Word 1.0Z">
<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="Ron Salmon">
</HEAD>

<BODY>
<P align=center><IMG SRC="gifs/logosm.gif" ALT="Chemist & Druggist logo"></P>
<H1 align=center><B>Market features 1996</B></H1>

<P>
A selection from <I>C&amp;D</I>'s regular market reviews for community
pharmacists planned for publication during 1996.
For details of special advertisement position availability 'phone
the Sales Team on 01732 364422. Pharmacists wishing to contribute
opinion or market experience are invited to write to the Editor,
or e-mail us on <A HREF="mailto:chemdrug@dotpharmacy.com.">chemdrug@dotpharmacy.com</A> 
<P>
January 13 <B>Feminine Hygiene</B> 
<P>
Sanpro products have been the focus for many changes in recent
years. We look at the size of the market and the winners and losers
there. Plus a review of intimate health problems.
<P>
January 20 <B>Shopfitting</B> 
<P>
Good layout and design are essential to effective retailing. We
bring pharmacists up to date with the latest shopfitting developments
plus aids to business, signage, merchandising and display.
<P>
February 3 <B>Diagnostics</B> 
<P>
There are many self-test kits on the market now, from cholesterol
to glucose. What's in the offing? And how can offering such in-store
services boost business?
<P>
February 10 <B>Skin Care</B> 
<P>
A comprehensive look at both cosmetic and medicated skin care
products.
<P>
February 17 <B>New Technology</B> 
<P>
A review of the latest computer developments within pharmacy,
retailing and the NHS.
<P>
March 2 <B>Sun Care</B> 
<P>
Despite the known dangers of the sun, consumers still want to
get a holiday tan. We look at ways to promote &quot;safe sun&quot;
and the latest products available.
<P>
March 9 <B>Staying Healthy</B> 
<P>
We investigate the complementary route to staying fit and healthy
in the Nineties. Herbal remedies, homoeopathy, aromatherapy and
other &quot;alternatives&quot; come into the spotlight.
<P>
March 23 <B>Photography</B> 
<P>
D&amp;P is big business through pharmacies. What services and
equipment are available? Plus a look at the cameras and film market.
<P>
April 6 <B>Mother and Babycare</B> 
<P>
Preconceptual and neo-natal care. The time between conception
and delivery is crucial for mothers-to-be. We give a guide to
pre- and post-pregnancy care, focusing on the needs of the newborn.
<P>
April 27 <B>Oral Hygiene</B> 
<P>
Brush up on what's new. With the move towards preventative care,
we look at the latest formulations and brush designs with a special
focus on electrical brushes.
<P>
May 4 <B>Hair Care</B> 
<P>
Crowning glory or disaster area? We investigate ways of boosting
hair care sales in pharmacy and evaluate the latest innovations.
<P>
May 18<B> Healthy Travel</B> 
<P>
Be it a case of the trots or a summer cold, a guide to staying
healthy on holiday - wherever customers go.
<P>
June 1 <B>Analgesics</B> 
<P>
The pharmacy is top location for pain relief purchases. We look
at the latest products that will keep it there. An examination
of both oral and topical analgesics.
<P>
June 15 <B> Body Beautiful</B> 
<P>
C&D's annual review of the body care market, for both men and women, looks at the edevelopments in bath and shower products, deodorants and depilatories.
<P>
July 6 <B>Sports & First Aid</B> 
<P>
Sports will be in the news this month with the Olympics in Atlanta. C&D reviews the wide range of products from topical analgesics to supports, which pharmacists are able to offer todays sports men and women. We will also be taking a look at first aid provision through the pharmacy  and what to recommend when presented with when presented with different kinds of injury.
<P>
July 20 <B>Eye Care</B> 
<P>
We reveal the latest developments in the eye care market, focusing on products ranging from washes to contact lens solutions. We also look at the profit potential of stocking reading glasses.
<P>
August 17 <B> Staying Healthy - Vitamins</B> 
<P>
The all-in-one/total care phenomenon is now hitting the VMS market. We'll be asking just how effective they are, compared to multi-pill popping
<P>
August 24 <B> Chemex Preview/Show Guide</B> 
<P>
We preview the latest news and the imminent product launches coming up at this year's Chemex show, 1-2 September 1996, at Olympia, London.
<P>
 September 14 <B>Men's Grooming</B> 
<P>
We'll be tracking down the latest in men's fragrances and taking a close look at the trend towards unisex products.  Shaving preps and shavers will also be under the microscope - including the electrical sector.
<P>
 October 5 <B>Care for the Elderly</B> 
<P>
C&D examines the growth in aids for the elderly and disabled and their potential as a profit centre in pharmacy.  We also look at conditions often seen in elderly patients, such as arthritis, incontinence and varicose veins and the products available to pharmacists to help sufferers.
<P>
 October 12 <B>Baby Care</B> 
<P>
 A focus on the professional care and advice pharmacists can offer new mothers.  We'll be investigating the latest developments in foods, feeding equipment and nappies.
<P>
October 26 <B>Indigestion Plus</B> 
<P>
Whether that troublesome stomach or bowel disorder is caused by excess acid, irritable bowel or diarrhoea, we'll be looking at the many causes and treatments.
<P>
 November 2 <B>Coughs & Colds</B> 
<P>
With winter barely upon us, C&D will focus on this key seasonal market.  With the increasing trend towards 'added plus'/'super' strength products, we ask where do we go from here?
<P>
November 16 <B>Specialist Nutrition</B> 
<P>
Be it gluten-, sugar- or allergy-free, C&D explores the different nutritional needs of certain sections of the community.  What is the healthiest diet for a diabetic and how can special products help coeliacs?
<P>
November 30 <B>Generics</B> 
<P>
C&D's special report on the market for generics:  views from manufacturers and health professionals.
<P>
 December 21 <B>Health Education</B> 
<P>
C&D advises pharmacists on setting up their own health video library;  plus advice on where to source educational leaflets and associated products.
<P>
<I>For further 1996 feature plans talk to the Sales Team on 01732
364422.</I> 
<P>
