<!doctype html public "-//IETF//DTD HTML//EN"><HTML><HEAD><TITLE>dotPHARMACY: Pharmacy Web links</TITLE><META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Word 1.0Z"><META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="Ron Salmon"></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR=#80FF80><BODY><A NAME="top"></A><P align=center><IMG SRC="gifs/logosm.gif" ALT="dotPHARMACY logo"></P><P><H1 align=center><B>Pharmacy Web site links</B></H1><P><P align=center><I>C&amp;D is currently contacting community pharmacists, manufacturers and others with sites on the World Wide Web of interest to theprofession and industry. Brief descriptions will be given of sitecontent, and hotlinks will be established where appropriate. Pleasekeep watching this page for new links.</I></P><HR><H2 align=center><STRONG>Pharmaceutical companies</STRONG></H2><H3><STRONG>Merck guide to preventable communicable diseases</STRONG></H3>Merck &amp; Co Inc include on their site notes for the public about the dangers and avoidance of preventable communicable diseases. Diseases covered at the time of review are chickenpox, hepatitis B, measles, mumps, rubella, haemophilus influenzae type b (relevant to recent meningitis concerns), and pneumococcal pneumonia. <A HREF="http://www.merck.com/disease/home.html">http://www.merck.com/disease/home.html</A><P>
<H3><strong>The Merck Manual</strong></H3>
Of more interest to pharmacists would beThe Merck Manual,  the book the company claims is the most widely  used medical text in the world, also available at the Merck site. You will be asked to register as you view. <A HREF="http://www.merck.com/pubs/">http://www.merck.com/pubs</A><P><H3><STRONG>Schering offer sympathetic advice for women</STRONG></H3>Schering Health Care UK Ltd have a developing site including advice sections which pharmacists could usefully print out for the benefit of women patients. The topics covered are "The Pill - myths and misconceptions", "How to examine your breasts" (with quick-loading line diagrams), and "About coloscopy". Also included on the site is a company history with beginings in a Berlin pharmacy in 1851. <A HREF="http://www.pavilion.co.uk/schering">http://www.pavilion.co.uk/schering</A>
<P>
<H3><STRONG>The Association of the British Pharmaceutical Industry</STRONG></H3>
The ABPI site provides background information on the trade association for more than 100 companies in Britain producing prescription medicines. There is a list of the member companies and links to their home pages as well as to a number of other useful sites. <A HREF="http://www.abpi.org.uk">http://www.abpi.org.uk</A>
<P>
<HR><H2 align=center><STRONG>Academic links</STRONG></H2><H3><STRONG>UK schools of pharmacy</STRONG></H3>This list is maintained by Dr David Temple at the Welsh School of Pharmacy, Cardiff, as part of the worldwide list he compiles for the International Pharmaceutical Federation. It includes contact names,  e-mail addresses and phone and fax numbers, with links to specialist sites run by some of the schools. <A HREF="http://info.cf.ac.uk/uwcc/phrmy/WWW-WSP/T-Z/UNIK.html">http://info.cf.ac.uk/uwcc/phrmy/WWW-WSP/T-Z/UNIK.html</A><P><H3><STRONG>Pharmacy sites worldwide</STRONG></H3><I>If you have all the time in the world, the worlds of pharmacy and medicine are here on the Internet for you to explore. Although all aspects of the professions may be catered for, academic content still forms the mainstay of most sites. On dotPHARMACY we will provide direct links to sites having direct relevance to UK community pharmacists and the industry, but the following can be recommended as starting points for joining the international scene</I>
<P>
<STRONG>Pharmaceutical Information Network</STRONG> (USA) at <A HREF="http://pharminfo.com/phrmlink.html">http://pharminfo.com/phrmlink.html</A>,<STRONG> PharmWeb </STRONG>(Manchester Universtity) which now has its own site at <A HREF="http://www.pharmweb.net">http://www.pharmweb.net</A> and<STRONG> World-wide Web Virtual Library: Pharmacy </STRONG>(Oklahoma University) at <A HREF="http://www.cpb.uokhsc.edu/pharmacy/pharmint.html">http://www.cpb.uokhsc.edu/pharmacy/pharmint.html</A> all have extensive directories and links.<P><STRONG>Pharmacy Mail Exchange</STRONG>, based at De Montfort University (Leicester), is a correspondence forum, so far used mainly for scientific discussion. Reach it on <A HREF="http://www.dmu.ac.uk/ln/pme/">http://www.dmu.ac.uk/ln/pme</A>.
<P>
The<STRONG> CyberRx Query Interface</STRONG> a search engine for pharmacy related resources at De Montfort, has been discontinued. All queries are being diverted to the PharmWeb site at <A HREF="http://www.pharmweb.net">http://www.pharmweb.net</A>.
<P>
Surfers in general have access to<STRONG> Search RxList</STRONG>, "the most comprehensive drug name cross-index on the Internet". This is a "fuzzy" search engine which finds close matches to incorrect spellings, and allows inclusion of a wildcard. Follow the trail from <A HREF="http://www.rxlist.com/">http://www.rxlist.com/</A><P><HR>
<P>
To be considered for inclusion on this page, submit details of your site to <A HREF="mailto:chemdrug@dotpharmacy.com">chemdrug@dotpharmacy.com</A><P><A HREF="#top">Top of page</A><P><P align=center><A HREF="http://www.dotpharmacy.co.uk/content1.html"><IMG SRC="gifs/contgrn1.gif" ALT="dotPHARMACY contents page"></A>
<P>
