 <HTML>

 <HEAD>

 <TITLE>FEDERAL GEOGRAPHIC DATA COMMITTEE </TITLE> <p>

 <H1>FACILITIES WORKING GROUP HOME PAGE </H1> <p>

 </HEAD>

 <BODY>


 <H4>The Facilities Working Group of the Federal Geographic Data
Committee (FGDC) was created in January 1995 and has met monthly to
address data issues that will enhance facility management.  A facility is
an entity with location which is deliberately established as a site for
designated activities.  A facility database might describe a factory,
military base, college, hospital, power plant, fishery, national park, office
building, space command center, or a prison. </H4> <p>

 <H3>*  <A HREF="./scope.html">Scope of the Facilities Working Group </A> </H3> <p>

 <H3>*  <A HREF="./current_poc.html">Membership Directory </A> </H3> <p>

 <H3>*  <A HREF="./data_standards.html">Current Facility Data Standards Activities </A> </H3> <p>

 <H3>* Minutes from Facilities Working Group meetings:  </H3>
 <UL>
	 <A HREF="./minutes/minutes_10-31-95.html">31 October 1995 </A> | 
	 <A HREF="./minutes/12-21-95.html">21 December 1995 </A> | 
	 <A HREF="./minutes/02-14-96.html">02 February 1996 </A> | 
	 <A HREF="./minutes/03-11-96.html">11 March 1996 </A> <br>
	 <A HREF="./minutes/04-08-96.html">08 April 1996 </A> | 
	 <A HREF="./minutes/05-13-96.html">13 May 1996 </A> |
 	 <A HREF="./minutes/06-17-96.html">17 June 1996 </A> |
 	 <A HREF="./minutes/07-15-96.html">15 July 1996 </A> |
	 <A HREF="./minutes/9-09-96.html"> 9 Sept 1996 </A> <br>
	 <A HREF="./minutes/10-07-96.html">7 Oct 1996 </A>
         
 </UL> <P>

 <H3>*  <A HREF="./next_meeting.html">The Next Meeting is 10 February, 1997 <P> </A> </H3>
 <P>
</ul>

 <H5>For more information about the Facilities Working Group contact: </H5>
 <pre>Mr. Moody K. Miles
Chair, Facilities Working Group
Headquarters, U.S. Army Corps of Engineers (HQUSACE)
ATTN: CECW-EP-S (M.K. Miles)
20 Massachusetts Avenue, NW
Washington, DC 20314-1000
Phone: 202-761-8885	Fax: 202-761-4002
Internet: <a href = "mailto:moody.miles@inet.hq.usace.army.mil">moody.miles@inet.hq.usace.army.mil </a> </pre>
