 <HTML>
<TITLE>SOUTH ATLANTIC DIVISION DATA PAGE </TITLE>

 <IMG ALIGN=MIDDLE SRC="../geo/images/coe.gif">  <P>
 <H3> USACE SOUTH ATLANTIC DIVISION DATA PAGE </H3>

 <IMG ALIGN=MIDDLE SRC="../geo/images/thin-bar.gif">
 <P>
 <P>
 <H3>
 <UL>
 <LI> To locate Division metadata files, please click on the area
of interest.  <P>

 <A HREF="http://corps_geo1.usace.army.mil/cgi-bin/imagemap/CESAD">
 <IMG ALIGN=MIDDLE SRC="../geo/images/cesad.gif" ismap>  </A>  <P>

 <LI> If you would like to view metadata related to other activities in the
Pacific Ocean Division please click on one of the following.
 </UL>
 </H5>

 <H3> Table of Contents  </H3>

 <H5> <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="../geo/images/redball.gif"> <A
HREF="cesad.collection.html"> Collection Metadata  </H5> </A>
A geospatial data "collection" is a logically consistent grouping of
geospatial data that can be documented in a uniform manner.  Each collection
will be established based on commonality of theme or based on commonality
of geospatial domain.

 <H5> <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="../geo/images/purpledot.gif"> <A
HREF="ftp://corps_geo1.usace.army.mil/sad/sad_data/metadata"> Detailed
Metadata </H5> </A>
A detailed metadata file is a FGDC compliant metadata file including all
applicable metadata elements.

 <H5> <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="../geo/images/blueball.gif"> <A
HREF="cesad.data.html"> Current/Planned Significant Data Development Efforts
 </H5>  </A>

 <H5> <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="../geo/images/orange.ball.gif"> <A
HREF="cesad.poc.html"> POC and other pertinent data sources in the
Division  </H5> </A>

 <IMG SRC="../geo/images/thin-bar.gif"> <p>
