||
 <a href = "#local-bottom">
Bottom of page</a>
||
 <a href = "../welcome.html#local-top">
USACE Geospatial Clearinghouse Title Page</a>
||
<hr>

 <img src = "../images/castle.gif" alt = "USACE Home Page">

 <h3>
National Geospatial Data Clearinghouse <br>
US Army Corps of Engineers Node</h3>

<h1>USACE Geospatial Data Server:<br>
Manual on how to submit and access data and metadata </h1>

<b>Version: 22 November 1996 </b><br>
(Note: When the data submission procedure is
 automated this manual will be revised.)
<p>
 <h3>
Table of contents
 </h3>

 <a href = "#intro">A. Introduction  </a>
 <p>
 <a href = "ht-gdspoc.html#local-top">
B. Responsibilities of the Geospatial Data and Systems 
Point of Contact (GD&S POC) </a>
 
 <p>
 <a href = "ht-submit.html#local-top">
C. Metadata submission to the Server
 </a>
 <dl>
 <dd>C1. Accessing the Server for metadata submission

<ul>
<li> <a href = "../user-id1.html">Register to submit 
     metadata and data.</a> (Also see other requirements 
     in this section.)
</ul>

 <dd>C2. Metadata file format
 <dd>C3. Filename conventions
 <dd>C4. Submitting metadata to the Server
 <dd>C5. Replacing or deleting metadata files
 </dl>
<p>
 <a href = "ht-dsubmit.html#local-top">
D. Data submission to the Server</a>
<dl>
<dd> D1. Accessing the Server for
           data submission
 <dd> D2. Submitting data
 <dd> D3. Details about ftp-ing
 <dd> D4. Replacing or deleting metadata files
  </dl>

<p>
 <a href = "ht-access.html#local-top">
E. Accessing Corps geospatial data and metadata</a>
 <dl>
 <dd> E1. USACE metadata
 <dd> E2. Accessing data via metadata:
      keyword search, image maps, USACE
      command list
 <dd> E3. Accessing Corps metadata using
      anonymous ftp
</dl>
<p>
<hr>
 <h3>
 <a name = "intro">
A.  Introduction
 </a>
 </h3>

The U.S. Army Corps of Engineers (USACE) has a server on the Internet on which they store and make available to all interested persons geospatial data and metadata. It is the USACE node of the National Geospatial Data Clearinghouse. Throughout this document the server is called the Geospatial Server or the Server.  Its network name is corps_geo1.usace.army.mil (IP address 144.3.144.20). It uses anonymous ftp, World Wide Web (WWW or web) and limited-access ftp processes to enable users to submit and access geospatial data and metadata.

 <p>
The multiple facets of the Server are described in this report, including:
 <p>
<ul>
<li>The process for submitting metadata to the Server
<p>
<li> The process for submitting geospatial <I>data</I> to the Server. When the process
of receiving data is automated on the Server this section will be revised.
<p>
<li>The processes to find and access data and metadata from the Server
<p>
<li>  The Geospatial Server WWW pages at
http://corps_geo1.usace.army.mil
 </ul>
 <hr>
