<hr>
 <img src = "../images/castle.gif" alt = "USACE Home Page">

 <h3>
USACE Geospatial Data Server:<br>
Manual on how to submit and access data and metadata </h3>

<h1>D.  Data submission to the Server </h1>

 <b>Version: 22 November 1996</b>
<p>

<h3>
Table of Contents
 </h3>


 <dl>
<dd> <a href = "#access">D1. Accessing the Server for
           data submission </a>
 <dd> <a href = "#submit">D2. Submitting data </a>
 <dd> <a href = "#ftp">D3. Details about ftp-ing</a>
 <dd> <a href = "#replace">D4. Replacing or deleting metadata files</a>
  </dl>

Please note that data and metadata files are currently being accepted on the Corps Geospatial Server. Read
<a href = "ht-submit.html">Section C</a> of this document for information about metadata submission procedures.
Corps personnel and  non-Corps people can search, view and obtain data and metadata by browsing  the WWW site, WAIS keyword searches and  anonymous ftp.  See 
<a href = "ht-access.html">Section E</a> for more information on accessing data and metadata.
<p>
If you have questions about anything in this document, you can ask your GD&S POC. If  you need further assistance, please email your questions or comments to the Server webmaster at
 
 <dl>
 <dd>
<a href = "mailto:webmaster@corps_geo1.usace.army.mil">
webmaster@corps_geo1.usace.army.mil</a>
 </dl>

 <p>
 <b>
 <a name = "access">
D1. Accessing the Server for data submission
 </a>
 </b>
 <br>
<p>
1. Inform the Geospatial Data and Systems (GD&S) POC for your organization that you  intend to submit data to the Server. The name and contact information for the GD&S POC of each USACE command is shown on the command's data page on the Server web site. You can get to a command's  data page via an
<a href = "../org.direct.html">alphabetical list</a>
or an 
<a href = "../metadata.html">image map</a>. A list of USACE GD&S POCs  is available for downloading in 
<a href = "ftp://corps_geo1.usace.army.mil/pub/gd_and_s/">
WordPerfect6.0 format</a> on the web site also. 
 <p>
2.  To put data files on the USACE Geospatial  Server you must get a Corps UPASS user id that is recognized by the Server. This is the same UPASS user id that is recognized for submitting metadata.  The Corps standard UPASS system will be used for issuing and controlling user ids and passwords.  To get a UPASS user id, ask your UPASS administrator for a "UPASS user id on the Geospatial Metadata and Data Server on corps_geo1." To find out who your UPASS administrator is, contact your information management group.
<p>
3.  The system administrator of the Geospatial Data Server must have your email address. If he already has your address because you have submitted metadata, you do not need to send it again. If you do need to send it you can use the <a href = "../user-id1.html">Corps_geo1 User-id Request Form</a> or email your email address with a message saying that you have requested access to the Server to

 <dl>
 <dd> 
<a href="mailto:webmaster@corps_geo1.usace.army.mil">
webmaster@corps_geo1.usace.army.mil</a>
 </dl>
<p>
 <b>
 <a name = "submit">
D2. Submitting data.
 </a>
 </b>
 <br>
The producers of geospatial data are responsible for the integrity, maintenance, and storage of the data that they produce. Data in any format will be accepted at this time. There are a few thing to do when submitting data.

<p>
1. You must use the extension .dat at the end of the filename. When you ftp the file to the Server you can make the name as long as you want and so can add the .dat to the filename you used on your PC. All filenames should consist of a <b>continuous</b> string of characters which may include  numbers, letters, underscore ( _ ), hyphen (-), and dot ( . ). Other special characters should be avoided.
<p>
2. A corresponding metadata file should be submitted at the same time or already be on the Server. The metadata file should have the same name as the data file, except have the extension .met instead of .dat.
<p>
3. Submit data by ftp-ing the data file to your home directory on the Server. (A brief description of ftp-ing is available in the section below for those who are not familiar with the process.)
<p>
4. Until the process of putting data on the Server is automated,  you <b><I>must </b></I> also send an email message to the webmaster (webmaster@corps_geo1.usace.army.mil) with your UPASS user id and the names of the data file and corresponding metadata file. 
<p>
 <b>
 <a name = "replace">
D3. Details about ftp-ing 
 </a>
 </b>
 <br>
<p>

To ftp a data file on the Geospatial Server, follow 
these steps.
 <p>
1. Plan your filename. Remember to use the .dat
extension for metadata file submissions.
<p>
2. Use your computer's ftp utility. There are many variations of ftp software. It would be impossible to describe them all. If you don't know how to use the ftp utility on your computer, you'll have to ask a knowledgeable neighbor or your desktop support team. 

<p>
3. You will need the following information to use ftp:  

The host computer you are ftp-ing to is
<dl>
 <dd>corps_geo1.usace.army.mil
 </dl>

The login id and password you will use are your UPASS user id and password. When you have successfully ftp'ed to corps_geo1, you will be in your home directory on the Server. This is the only place on the Server where you can put files. 

 <p>
5. To submit the data file, you will use the <I>copy</I> or <I>put</I> function in your ftp software. 
You can submit multiple files during one session.
 
<p>
6. When you are done putting data on the Server, close the session and exit from the ftp software. If you stop communicating with the ftp site for some period of time during the ftp session,
you may be "timed out," i.e. you will not be connected to the Server anymore.  If this occurs you will have to ftp to the Server again.

 <p>
 <b>
 <a name = "replace">
D4. Replacing or deleting data files 
 </a>
 </b>
 <br>
To replace or delete a data file, you will need to
know the exact filename of the file to be replaced or 
deleted. You can use anonymous ftp to go to your
organization's data directory to look for the filename you need.
(Login procedures for anonymous ftp are 
different from the UPASS user id login.  Directions for logging into
anonymous ftp, listing filenames, and viewing ASCII files are given
below in Section E3, Accessing Corps data and metadata. )
<p>
Until the automatic system is set up to accept data, to replace or delete data you should contact the webmaster at 
<a href = "mailto:cadams@crrel.usace.army.mil">
cadams@crrel.usace.army.mil</a> or 603-646-4320.

 <p>
