<HTML><BODY><H1>Facility Working Group Data Standards Activities</H1><p>
<p>
 <H1></H1><P>
&nbsp; <P>
<I>Please note: to download the linked files, some browsers may require you to Shift-click the link.</I>
<p>
&nbsp; <P>
<B>1. Development of a Facility ID Data Standard.</B>   This effort was approved by the FGDC Standards Working Group.  The scope of the effort is to develop a Facility ID data standard that supports identification of place-based objects that are generally known as facilities.  Details for this effort are included in the <B><A HREF="facility/fid.pro">proposal</A></B> that was submitted to the Standards Working Group as well as a <B><A HREF="facility/fid-dft.wp6"> draft base document for the standard</A></B>.  <p>
<p>
If you are interested in working on the development of this standard contact <B><A HREF="mailto:bargmeyer.bruce@epamail.epa.gov">Mr. Bruce Bargmeyer</A></B>, project team leader.<p>
<P>
There are two <A Href="reflector.html">email lists</A> established to facilitate communication with this group.
<p>
<p>
&nbsp; <P>
<B>2. Development of a Utilities Geospatial Data Content Standard.  </B>This effort was approved by the FGDC Standards Working Group. The scope of the effort is to develop a nationally focused Utilities Geospatial Data Content Standard that supports intra-city applications such as large-scale engineering and life-cycle maintenance of utility systems.  Details for this effort are included in the <B><A HREF="facility/utility.pro">proposal</A></B> that was submitted to the FGDC Standards Working Group.<p>
<p>
The Facilities Working Group project team for this standard has extracted the attributes, entities, domains, and domain values from the utility portion of the <B><A HREF="http://fwgcom.wes.army.mil/projects/standard/tssds/">Tri-Service CADD/GIS Technology Center's Tri-Service Spatial Data Standards (TSSDS)</A></B> as a first draft of a national standard.  Files containing these attributes, entities, domains, and domain values are: <p>
<p>
<B><A HREF="facility/utilatt.zip">utilatt.zip</A> | <A HREF="facility/utildom.zip">utildom.zip</A> | <A HREF="facility/utilent.zip">utilent.zip</A> | <A HREF="facility/utilval.zip">utilval.zip</A></B>  -- compressed<p>
<B><A HREF="facility/utilatt.rtf">utilatt.rtf</A> | <A HREF="facility/utildom.rtf">utildom.rtf</A> | <A HREF="facility/utilent.rtf">utilent.rtf</A> | <A HREF="facility/utilval.rtf">utilval.rtf</A></B>  -- rich text format <p>
<p>
If you are interested in working on the development of this standard contact <B><A HREF="mailto:kbacke@tec.army.mil">Mr. Kevin Backe</A></B>, project team leader.<p>
<p>
<p>
&nbsp; <P>
<B>3. Development of an Environmental Hazards Geospatial Data Content Standard.</B>  The FGDC Standards Working Group asked that the Facilities Working Group revise its proposal for development of this standard. The scope of the effort is to develop a nationally focused Environmental Hazards Geospatial Data Content Standard that supports the study, management, and remediation of hazardous waste.  A project team is working on the required revisions to the proposal, however general details for this effort are included in the first <B><A HREF="facility/envhaz.pro">proposal</A></B> that was submitted to the Standards Working Group.<p>
<p>
If you are interested in working on the development of this standard contact <B><A HREF="mailto:bargmeyer.bruce@epamail.epa.gov">Mr. Bruce Bargmeyer</A></B>, project team leader.<p>
<p>
<p>
&nbsp; <P>
<B>4. Development of an SDTS/FIPS 173 CADD Profile.</B>  This effort was approved by the FGDC Standards Working Group. The scope of the effort is to develop a profile for the Spatial Data Transfer Standard/Federal Information Processing Standard 173 (SDTS/FIPS 173) to support the exchange and transfer of CADD spatial data.  Details for this effort are included in the <B><A HREF="facility/sdtscadd.pro">proposal</A></B> that was submitted to the Standards Working Group.  <p>
<p>
Under the auspices of the Facilities Working Group, the Tri-Service CADD/GIS Technology Center investigated this topic.  This work began prior to finalization of  the FGDC standards development process.  Their findings are summarized in: <B><A HREF="facility/cadd-aut.wp6">Development of a Spatial Data Transfer Standard (SDTS) Profile for the Translation of AutoCAD&reg; CADD Elements</A></B> and <B><A HREF="facility/cadd-int.wp6">Development of a Spatial Data Transfer Standard (SDTS) Profile for the Translation of MicroStation CADD Elements</A></B>.<p>
<p>
<p>
If you are interested in working on the development of this standard contact <B><A HREF="mailto:kbacke@tec.army.mil">Mr. Kevin Backe</A></B>, project team leader.<p>
<p>
<p>
&nbsp; <P>
<B>5. Development of an Accuracy Standard for Facility Mapping.</B>   The FGDC Standards Working Group approved a multi-part accuracy standard and Part 4 will be related to facility mapping.  The U.S. Army Corps of Engineers Standard for facility mapping is being revised to meet the needs of a broader community and a <B><A HREF="facility/fgcs-pt4-y12.wp6">draft version</A></B> is available for comment and review.  <p>
<p>
If you are interested in working on the development of this standard contact <B><A HREF="mailto:kbacke@tec.army.mil">Mr. Kevin Backe</A></B>, project team leader.<p>
<p>
<p>
<p>
<B><i>(Public reviews are conducted as part of the FGDC standards development process.  However the standard development project team leaders welcome your comments prior to the public review.)</i><p>
</B></BODY></HTML>
</DOC>
