 <HTML>
 <HEAD>
 <TITLE>Minutes from 9 September, 1996 </TITLE>
 <H1>Minutes </H1>
 </HEAD>

 <BODY>
Summary Report


<H3>Federal Geographic Data Committee (FGDC)
Facilities Working Group Meeting
9 September 1996
</H3>
<H4>
Headquarters, U.S. Army Corps of Engineers (USACE)
Pulaski Building, Washington, DC
</H4>


1)  Persons Attending:  <A HREF="./9-09-96.attach1.html">Attendance roster</A> <P>

* See <A HREF="./9-09-96.attach2.html">agenda.</A> <P>

2)  Update on FGDC Activities - M.K. Miles/Kevin Backe (USACE): 
<UL>
 <LI>The Coordination Group met on 9 September.  GIS/LIS is 16-22 November in Denver, CO and if anyone has any FGDC-related information that they would like displayed at the FGDC booth, contact Ms Jennifer Fox at 703-648-5514.  There was an update on activities of the Clearinghouse Working Group.  The Working Group is still recommending a move from WAIS to Isite as the public domain search and query tool for the Clearinghouse.  The Group is pursuing ways to improve searches such as listing the keywords to query on for each agency's Clearinghouse metadata.  The Coordination Group prepared for the FGDC Steering Group meeting which is scheduled for 11 September.  Agenda items for that meeting include NSDI Strategic Plan, FGDC and State Council cooperative efforts, and the recent Hammer Award to the FGDC from Vice-President Gore.
  <LI>The Standards Working Group (SWG) met on 9 September.  The Soils Geographic Data Standard, the Geospatial Positioning Accuracy Standard, the National Standard for Spatial Data Accuracy, the SDTS Point Profile, and the Vegetation Classification and Information Standard are all being reviewed by the SWG prior to going forward for a public review.  The Cadastral Data Content Standard and the Classification of Wetlands and Deep Water Habitats standard are being reviewed by the SWG prior to final FGDC endorsement. 
<LI> Mr. Backe discussed the FGDC Soils Subcommittee=s draft Soils Geographic Data Standard with the FWG. The current draft of this standard tends to be agronomy-based and was intended to contain only surface soils characteristics.  However,  engineering application require the capture of geotechnical characteristics of soils (which apparently is not containing in the FGDC Soils Standard.) 
<LI> Mr. Backe discussed the comments generated by the SWG review of the Geospatial Positioning Accuracy Standard proposal and draft standard.  The SWG directed the Base Cartographic Subcommittee and the Geodetic Control Subcommittee to consider merging the National Standard for Spatial Data Accuracy into the Geospatial Positioning Accuracy Standard prior to sending these two standards out for public review.  The Geospatial Positioning Accuracy Standard is planned to be a multi-part standard addressing many aspects of positional accuracy including a part specifically to support positional accuracy for engineering, construction and facility management applications.
<LI>The SWG discussed and approved holding an additional meeting approximately once a quarter to allow for presentations on FGDC standards projects and proposals.  This will likely be the forum that the four recent proposals from the FWG will be presented to and discussed. 
<LI> Mr. Billy Tolar, FGDC Metadata Coordinator, discussed the pursuit of Astandard@ or recommended metadata implementations for the Framework Working Group and others.  There have been several Federal Agencies and the Framework Working Group that have requested the FGDC Secretariat develop a Astandard@ implementation that could then be queried and accessed by a single software capability.  The use of this Astandard@ implementation by an agency or geospatial application community would be optional and could be considered a guideline or specification. 
<LI> The SWG discussed the draft a set of rules for the subcommittees and working groups to use when opening their meetings to non-Federal participation.  Mr. Fred Broome, Census Bureau and Cultural and Demographic Subcommittee, will finalize these rules per comments from this discussion. 
<LI> ACTION:  Mr. Backe will forward a message about the FWG concerns about the current draft of the FGDC Soils standard to the SWG (Mr. Backe).
</UL>

3)  Proposal for a Utilities Data Content Standard (Kevin Backe, USACE):  
<UL>
<LI> Mr. Backe stated there was no change in status from the last meeting for this project.  The SWG has received the proposal for this project but has not formally reviewed this proposal.  Mr. Backe made another call for FWG participants for a Utilities project team.  To date no participants have volunteered to participate on this project.
Mr. Rik Wiant commented that he was unable to decipher the email message that contained the Utilities database information.  Mr. Backe stated he would send the FWG an email that directed members how to pull the information down from the FWG homepage.   
<LI>Messrs Backe and Miles recommended a six month development period for this standard which began in August 1996.  Ms Davis (FEMA), Mr. Britton (NASA), Mr. Wilson (APWA), and Mr. Ou (FS) expressed an interest in having members of their organization participate in this project. 
<LI> Ms Leslie Godwin (Census Bureau) forwarded comments to Ms Capps on the Utilities, Facility ID, and Environmental Hazards Standards that have been proposed by the FWG.  Since Ms Godwin was unable to attend the meeting, discussion on her comments was deferred until the next meeting. 
<LI> ACTION: Provide Mr. Backe with name(s) and contact information for individuals that will participate on the Utilities Project team to develop the standard (Mr. Britton, Ms. Davis, Mr. Ou, Mr. Wilson). 
<LI>ACTION: Provide specific information about how to access the Utilities database information from the FWG homepage (Mr. Backe).
</UL>

4)  Modeling the Utilities Entity Set (Chip Fleming, Tri-Service Center): 
<UL>
<LI> Mr. Fleming discussed a joint project between the Center and the HQUSACE Information Management Directorate to develop DOD/USACE compliant data models using the IDEF1X modeling language.  The initial project goal has focused on modeling the 12+ entity classes from the TSSDS utilities entity set.  Once these Utilities models are complete they will become part of the USACE Data Repository.  The USACE data encyclopedia=s utilities data elements may also be used to standardize geospatial utilities data model for the DOD Data Element Standardization program.  
<LI> Mr. Fleming stated that there would be a number of changes to the Utilities Entity Set in version 1.6 of the TSSDS (Oct. 96).  These changes will effect this modeling effort and may also effect the FWG Utilities Data Content standard effort.
</UL>

5)  Proposal for Environmental Hazards Content Standard (Kevin Backe, USACE):  
<UL>
<LI> Mr. Backe stated there was no change in status from the last meeting on this project.  The SWG has received the proposal for this project but has not formally reviewed this proposal.  Mr. Backe also made another call for FWG participants on a Environmental Hazards project team.  To date no names have been forwarded to Mr. Backe for volunteers to participate on this project.  Messrs Miles and Backe suggested a nine month development period for this project which began in August 1996.   
<LI> ACTION: Provide Mr. Backe with name(s) and contact information for individuals that will participate on the Environmental Hazards Project team.(FWG members).  
</UL>

6)  FIPS 173/SDTS CADD Profile Proposal and Project Status (Kevin Backe, USACE): 
<UL>
<LI> Mr. Backe stated that the proposal for the development of a Federal Information Processing Standard 173/Spatial Data Transfer Standard (FIPS 173/SDTS) CADD Profile was forwarded to the SWG for consideration.  Mr. Backe briefly discussed the two reports generated by the Center in support of this activity.  These reports  examined the translation of Microstation and AutoCAD CADD elements into SDTS elements and provide a discussion of some of the new elements and changes to SDTS to accommodate a CADD profile.  Mr. Backe also discussed the potential development of a simple vector profile for SDTS and the possible relationship of this activity with a CADD profile. 
</UL>

7)   Next Meeting: 
<UL>
<LI> The next meeting will be 7 October from 1-4 in Room 8222D of the Pulaski Building, 20 Massachusetts Avenue, NW, Washington, DC. 
</UL>
</BODY>
</HTML>


