<HEAD>
<TITLE> Minutes from 7 Oct, 1996 </TITLE>
<H1> Minutes </H1>
</HEAD>

<BODY>
Summary Report
<H3>
Federal Geographic Data Committee (FGDC)
Facilities Working Group (FWG) Meeting
7 October 1996
</H3>
<H4>

       Headquarters, U.S. Army Corps of Engineers (USACE)
                Pulaski Building, Washington, DC

</H4>

1)  Persons Attending: <A HREF="./10-07-96.attach1.html"> Attendance roster and POC information is </A> <P>

* See <A HREF="./10-07-96.attach2.html">  agenda </A> <P>


2) Update on FGDC Activities - Penny Capps/Kevin Backe (USACE):
<UL>

<LI>   The Steering Group met on 11 September.   Secretary Babbitt
accepted a Hammer Award for the FGDC.  These awards are given by
Vice-President Gore for demonstrating excellence in reinventing
government, cutting costs, etc.  Each FGDC member will receive
their own hammer award.  In order to continue to strategize on
improved communication between the FGDC and the non-Federal
sector, cooperative projects will be briefed at each FGDC
meeting.  The FGDC members also discussed the NSDI Strategic Plan
and tasked the Coordination Group to provide agencies with a
template to complete that describes their compliance with the
Plan and to schedule presentations on some of these plans at the
next Steering meeting.
 <LI> The Coordination Group and the Standards Working Group (SWG)
met on 6 September.  Activities of these 2 groups were briefed at
the 9 September FWG meeting.
 <LI> The Standards Working Group Proposal Review Team met on 4
October.  The following FWG proposals for standards development
were approved (with minor revisions requested) at this meeting:
Utilities Data Content Standard, Facility ID Standard, and SDTS
CADD Profile.  The review team asked the FWG to better define the
scope of the proposal for an Environmental Hazards Data Content
Standard and resubmit it.  Other proposals for standards
development that were approved are: Thematic Supplement for
Geospatially References Cultural and Demographic Data Metadata;
Address (physical, not email) Content Standard; Digital Elevation
Data; and Digital Orthoimagery. 
<LI>     The Cartographic and the Geodetic Control Subcommittees are
to consider merging the National Standard for Spatial Data
Accuracy into the Geospatial Positioning Accuracy Standard prior
to sending these two standards out for public review.  The
Geospatial Positioning Accuracy Standard is planned to be a multi-
part standard addressing many aspects of positional accuracy
including a part specifically to support positional accuracy for
engineering, construction and facility management applications.
</UL>
<P>
3) Status of FWG Proposals and Next Steps (Kevin Backe, USACE):
<UL>
<LI>  Utilities Content Standard.  The SWG Standards Proposal
Review Team approved this proposal but asked for some minor
revisions, primarily clarification of inter- and intra-city
applications. The reviewers would like to see the scope expanded,
if it will not be too much extra work, to include intercity
utilities.  Mr. Backe will reword this section and return it to
the SWG.  Thus far the development team for this standard
consists of: Mr. Kevin Backe (USACE, coordinator), Mr. Fong Ou
(Forest), Mr. Keith Britton (NASA), Ms Carolyn Davis (FEMA), Mr.
Kern Wilson (APWA), Mr. Dan McHugh (NY, MTA), Mr. Rich Grady
(Applied Geographics), Mr. Bruce Bargmeyer (EPA), and Mr. Jim
Rossberg (ASCE).
<LI>     Mr. McHugh asked if communications were going to be included
in the Utilities Standard and Ms Capps reminded the group that at
a previous meeting, the group decided to exclude communications
from this standard and submit it separately.
<LI>     Mr. Rossberg said that the American Society of Civil
Engineers (ASCE) formed a Utility Committee and they are working
on standards.  He will help this group and the FWG to exchange
information.
<LI>     ACTION: Reword Utilities Content Proposal and return to SWG
(Mr. Backe).
<LI>     ACTION: Revise FWG homepage info on activities and announce
to FWG when this is available (Ms Capps).
<LI>     ACTION: Provide Mr. Backe with name(s) and contact
information for individuals that will participate on the
Utilities Project team to develop the standard, ASAP (FWG
Members).
<LI>     ACTION: Provide an article on the FWG to Mr. Rossberg for
inclusion in the ASCE newsletter (Ms Capps).
<LI>     ACTION: Provide ASCE Utility Standard to Mr. Backe (Mr.
Rossberg).

<LI> Environmental Hazards Content Standard.  The proposal for the
Environmental Hazards Geospatial Data Content Standard was not
approved by the standards review team because the objectives and
scope are unclear, i.e. What environmental hazards are being
standardized? Is the standard limited to only hazardous waste
sites? The standards review team also thought it is  unclear what
involvement regulatory agencies, like  EPA, would have in the
development of the standard.  A project team to rewrite the
proposal consists of:  Mr. Bruce Bargmeyer (EPA, coordinator) and
Mr. Kevin Backe (USACE).
<LI>     The FWG proposed that the project team discuss the following
items: should sound and electromagnetic pollution be considered
(Mr. Rik Wiant, USACE)?  ASCE maps the probability of
hazards/natural disasters per an ASCE standard 795 but they
should not be included in this environmental hazards standard
(Mr. Rossberg), consider EPA requirements (Mr. Backe).
<LI>     ACTION: Edit the proposal, present to FWG for approval, and
resubmit to the SWG (Mr. Bargmeyer).
<LI>     ACTION: Provide Mr. Bargmeyer with name(s) and contact
information for individuals that will participate on the Facility
ID Project team to develop the standard (FWG Members).


<LI> SDTS CADD Profile.  The proposal for this standard was
approved by the SWG Review Team on the condition that minor edits
were made. Mr. Backe will make the requested changes and
resubmit.  Substantial work has already been performed by the Tri-
Service CADD/GIS Technology Center and its contractor(s).  The
FWG does not need to create a project team for this effort but
all members will be provided with reports to review and
opportunities to recommend approaches to profile development.  As
soon as the final reports from the contractor are available they
will be posted on the FWG homepage and distributed at the next
FWG meeting.   ACTION: Edit the proposal and resubmit to the SWG
(Mr. Backe).
<LI>     ACTION: Provide the FWG copies of the SDTS CADD Profile
reports (Ms Capps).

<LI>  Facility ID Standard.  The proposal for this standard was
approved, with a request for some modifications.  Mr. Bargmeyer
will reword the proposal to clarify that the standard will not
assign specific ID numbers to specific facilities, rather it will
assist in linking related place-based facility objects.  He will
also clarify that the standard will not focus on a common list of
facility ids (although this is a result of implementing the
standard) but the development of a schema.  He will also list who
expects to benefit from this standard.  Mr McHugh remarked that
he convinced the NY GIS Steering Committee to accommodate fields
for Ids in its efforts.
<LI>     Thus far the development team for this standard consists of:
Mr. Bargmeyer (EPA, coordinator), Mr. McHugh (NY, MTA), Ms Davis
(FEMA), Mr. Backe (USACE), Mr. Wilson (APWA), Mr. Wiant (USACE),
Ms Dee McFadden-Wallace (GSA), and Mr. Rossberg (ASCE).
<LI>     ACTION: Edit the proposal and resubmit to the SWG (Mr.
Bargmeyer).
<LI>     ACTION: Provide Mr. Bargmeyer with name(s) and contact
information for individuals that will participate on the Facility
ID Project team to develop the standard (FWG Members).
</UL>
<P>
4) Schedule for Future FWG Meetings (Capps): The FWG decided to
try meeting every other month instead of monthly.  The standards
project teams will meet/teleconference/email as needed and report
progress at each FWG meeting.
<P>     

5) Misc.:  GIS/LIS is 16-22 November in Denver, CO.  Contact Ms
Jennifer Fox at 703-648-5514 if you have FGDC-related information
that you would like displayed at the FGDC booth.
<P>
Mr. Wiant asked if agencies were making any progress on
converting to metric.  Mr. McHugh was the only member who
mentioned implementations.  Messrs Wiant and McHugh continued
their discussions after the meeting.
<P>

6) Next Meeting: The next meeting will be 9 December from 1-3 in
Room 8124C of the Pulaski Building, 20 Massachusetts Avenue, NW,
Washington, DC. The Facility ID and Environmental Hazards
Standards Development Teams will meet from 10-12 (same day, same
room) and the Utilities Standard Project Team will meet from 3:15-
4:15 (same day, same room).  Mr. Skip Kiem (MTL Systems, Inc.)
will brief the Mobile Information Distribution and Support
Systems (MIDAS) at the next FWG meeting.
<P>

</BODY>
</HTML>
</DOC>
