 <HTML>
 <HEAD>
 <TITLE>Minutes from 13 May, 1996 </TITLE>
 <H1>Minutes </H1>
 </HEAD>

 <BODY>
Summary Report


<H3>Federal Geographic Data Committee (FGDC)
Facilities Working Group Meeting 
13 May 1996 
</H3>
<H4>
Headquarters, U.S. Army Corps of Engineers (USACE)
Pulaski Building, Washington, DC
</H4>


1)  Persons Attending:  <A HREF="./05-13-96.attatch1.html">Attendance roster.</A> <P> 

* See <A HREF="./05-13-96.attatch2.html">agenda. </A> <P>


2)  Update on FGDC Activities - M.K. Miles (USACE): 
<UL>
<LI>The Steering Group  met on 30 April and the primary agenda item was developing state councils and partnerships.
<LI>The Coordination Group held a meeting on 9 April and discussed the 1996 Competitive Cooperative Agreement Program (CCAP). A Land Cover Working Group was approved for a one year trial period.
<LI>The Standards Working Group (SWG) held an FGDC-wide meeting on 9 April. 
<UL>
<LI>Ms Denise Perreca  discussed the recommendations from the report on activities of the FGDC Subcommittees and Working Groups.  
<LI>Mr. Richard Hogan (C/SWG) made a presentation on the SDTS/FIPS 173 logical data model and suggested that FGDC Subcommittees and Working Groups use this model.  
<LI>Mr. Miles briefed a proposal that the Tri-Service Spatial Data Standards (TSSDS) structure and database development tool be adopted as an FGDC standard.  
<LI>Mr. Ed Riegelmann (Tri-Service Center) made a presentation on the TSSDS and a strawman of an FGDC version.  This tool uses an interactive approach (Microsoft Access) and would support query and analysis of overlapping standards, and would enable distribution of FGDC standards in a consistent and integrated format on one CD.
</UL>
<LI>At the 14 May meeting of the SWG, a prototype phase of the proposal was approved.  The Center will integrate the appropriate parts of the following data content and classification standards:
<UL>
<LI>Base Carto (DLG-E)
<LI>Vegetation
<LI>Cadastral
<LI>Wetlands
</UL>
Some large scale features of the TSSDS will also be included to demonstrate the ability of the tool to flag potential overlaps.
</UL>

3)  Proposal of Utilities and Environmental Hazards Entities of the TSSDS as Facilities Working Group Standards (Harold Smith and Bobby Carpenter, Tri-Service Center/Kevin Backe USACE):
<UL>
<LI>At the last meeting the Facilities Working Group agreed to review the TSSDS Utilities, Buildings, Improvements, Communications, and Environmental Hazards entity classes and recommend changes or recommend that these sections be initiated into the FGDC standards development process.  Some members had reviewed portions of some of these entities.  Mr. Miles suggested that we might make more progress if we start with one entity such as Utilities.
<LI>Mr. Backe provided an overview of a proposal to develop FGDC Utilities and Environmental Hazards Data Content Standards.  Mr. Backe recommended that the Facilities Working Group establish project teams to develop these standards.  Mr. Backe also discussed the steps to develop an FGDC standard (defined in the FGDC Standards Reference Model).  
<LI>Mr. Carpenter provided an overview of the TSSDS and a presentation on the environmental hazards entities.  
<LI>Mr. Smith briefed the Utilities entities.   
<LI>ACTION:  Draft proposals for an FGDC Utilities and Environmental Hazards Data Content Standards.  Send out a request for participants for the Utilities and Environmental Hazards project teams (Kevin Backe).
</UL>

4)  Development of a Unique Identification Number (UIN) Standard for Facilities (Bruce Bargmeyer, EPA):
<UL>
<LI>At the last meeting, a small group agreed to write a proposal for a Facility UIN Standard.  Mr. Bargmeyer provide copies of the subject draft proposal at the meeting for review and comment.   He also provided the group an overview of the subject proposal.  Mr. Bargmeyer recommended the following approach be taken:
<UL>
<LI>assign a UIN that is non-intelligent to geospatial objects of interest
<LI>associate this UIN with other agency/organization identifiers by linking these existing identifier (e.g., GSA, DOD, Army, Navy, Air Force identifiers) to this UIN	
<LI>associate the UIN with a core set of identifying information (e.g., proper name, lat/lon, type of facility) which potentially links to geospatial information in other databases.  
</UL>
<LI>ACTION: Send comments to Mr. Bargmeyer for incorporation into the proposal and be prepared to continue discussions at next meeting (All Facilities Working Group Members).  
</UL>

5)  Misc.:
<UL>
<LI>Group members asked for a reminder about the meeting, 1 week in advance.
<LI>ACTION: Email/fax members a reminder about the meetings (Penny Capps).
</UL>

6)  Next Meetings:
<UL>
	<LI>The next meetings will be 17 June and 15 July from 1-4 in Room 8222D of the Pulaski Building, 20 Massachusetts Avenue, NW, Washington, DC. 
</UL

</BODY>
</HTML>
