 <HTML>
 <HEAD>
 <TITLE>Minutes from 13 May, 1996 </TITLE>
 <H1>Minutes </H1>
 </HEAD>

 <BODY>
Summary Report


<H3>Federal Geographic Data Committee (FGDC)
Facilities Working Group Meeting
15 July 1996
</H3>
<H4>
Headquarters, U.S. Army Corps of Engineers (USACE)
Pulaski Building, Washington, DC
</H4>
 
 
1)  Persons Attending:  <A HREF="./07-15-96.attatch1.html">Attendance roster.</A> <P>  
 
* See <A HREF="./07-15-96.attatch2.html">agenda. </A> <P> 
 
 
2)  Update on FGDC Activities - Penny Capps/Kevin Backe (USACE):  
<UL>
<LI>The Coordination Group met on 9 July.  If you would like a copy of the entire FGDC membership directory contact Ms Mickey Kilpatrick at 703-648-4636 (COMM), 703-648-5725 (FAX), or mkilpatr@usgs.gov (Internet).  She can provide you a custom sorted membership list by agency, subcommittee, etc. 
<LI>Mr. Peter Lyttle, with the USGS Office of Outreach, has agreed to write a monthly column for Geotimes Magazine featuring maps published by the Federal Government.  These are Ageologic@ maps in the very broadest use of the term, i.e. not just geology but surveying, imagery, etc.   
<LI>The FGDC Secretariat will send a letter to State Geospatial Data Councils requesting their participation in data standards development.  The letter will ask them to contact the subcommittee or working group chairs for information about particular standards.  This might assist the Facilities Working Group in obtaining a broader review of its utilities, environmental, and unique feature ID standards. 
<LI>There will be another Framework FY96 Pilot Project Managers meeting in Baltimore this month.  They will continue their discussions on experiences in developing some aspect of the Framework.  This week a team of Feds is reviewing proposals for FY97 Framework Projects.  The FGDC is beginning discussions on what the Federal Government should do next in order to develop the Framework, i.e. let each agency do its own thing, develop a standard approach, etc. 
<LI>The Standards Working Group (SWG) met on 9 July. The Cadastral Subcommittee is making its final changes on the Cadastral Standard and then it will be presented to the Coordination and Steering Groups for final approval.  Then it will be a Federal Standard!  It is posted on the FGDC public ftp site. 
<LI>The Geodetic Control Subcommittee has asked for reviewers for the Geospatial Positioning Accuracy Standard.  This is available in the Geodetic directory on the Standards Working Group ftp site.  There are supposed to be 4 parts to this standard and accuracy standards for large scale facility mapping is one of those sections. 
<LI>The Soils Subcommittee revised the Soils Standard based on comments and it needs to be reviewed again by the Standards Group before it goes out for public review.  Check the Soil directory of the Standards Working Group page.  The first version was agronomy based and the Tri-Service CADD/GIS Technology Center submitted a request for geotechnical and engineering parameters to be added.  Mr. Dan McHugh (NY City MTA) said that this is an important revision for his geospatial data community. 
<LI>The Vegetation Standard is out for public review and is posted on the FGDC public ftp site. 
<LI>The Wetlands Standard will be sent to the Standards Working Group on 1 August for a review before final endorsement. 
<LI>Mr. Billy Tolar, Metadata Standard Manager, discussed the pursuit of metadata profiles.  These profiles would be optional and would provide a template for specific data communities to follow if so desired.  These profiles would augment the Metadata Standard. 
<LI>Mr. Fred Broome, Census Bureau and Cultural and Demographic Subcommittee, is establishing a group to draft a set of rules for the subcommittees and working groups to use when opening their meetings to non-Federal participation.  The Facilities Working Group has not had any issues with opening its meetings but some subcommittees are concerned about voting, possible overwhelming attendance, etc. 
</UL> 

3)  Proposal for a Utilities Data Content Standard (Kevin Backe, USACE):
<UL>
<LI> Mr. Backe modified the Tri-Service Spatial Data Standards (TSSDS) Utility entity set for consideration as a Federal standard.  He removed Tri-Service specific information as well as implementation specific information.  He provided an example of this version in paper form and will provide a digital version to those interested.  Ms Capps will also make the electronic version available on the Facilities Working Group page.  Mr. Backe is looking for volunteers to continue developing the standard. <BR>
<LI>The <A HREF="./07-15-96.attatch3.html">proposal</A> for an FGDC Utilities Data Content Standard was approved by the Facilities Working Group and will be submitted to the Standards Working Group.  This signifies the intent to develop a standard.  <BR>
<LI>Mr. Tony Joyce (NAVFAC) expressed concern that we do not have enough variety of people developing the standard, specifically utility companies.  Ms Capps explained that the Facilities Working Group meetings are announced on the World Wide Web and in the Federal Register so that anyone may attend.  Although there has been limited non-Federal attendance at the meetings, Ms Capps said that she receives email and phone calls from non-Federal members who are on the distribution list but are not able to attend the meetings.  They are interested in the Utilities Standard and plan to keep abreast of its development.  There is always room for improving our coordination and Ms Capps is willing to distribute information to any person or agency.    <BR>
<LI>Mr. Fong Ou (Forest Service) provided a list of entities that he would like added to the Draft Utility Standard.  Mr. Backe asked that anyone requesting entities be added also provide the definitions of those entities, as well as associated attributes and domains.<BR>
<LI>ACTION: Submit the Proposal for a Utilities Data Content Standard to the Standards Working Group (Mr. M.K. Miles).   
<LI>ACTION: Provide electronic copies of the draft standard to those interested (Mr. Kevin Backe). 
<LI>ACTION: Serve the electronic version of the draft standard on the Facilities Working Group Page (Ms Penny Capps). 
<LI>ACTION: Inform Mr. Backe if you would like to be on the Utilities Project team to develop the standard (Facilities Working Group Members).  
<LI>ACTION: Provide Ms Capps with individuals or agencies that you would like added to the distribution list (Facilities Working Group Members). 
<LI>ACTION: Provide Mr. Backe with specific information about the entities to be added (Mr. Ou). 
<LI>ACTION: Provide IDEF Model of Utilities Standard at next meeting (Mr. Harold Smith). 
</UL>
4)  Proposal for Environmental Hazards Content Standard (Penny Capps, USACE):
<UL>
<LI>Ms Capps presented the revised <A HREF="./07-15-96.attatch4.html">proposal</A> for an FGDC Environmental Hazards Data Content Standard.  Mr Joyce was concerned that we would duplicate the efforts of the Chemical Abstract Society and suggested rewriting the proposal to say that we would not duplicate the efforts of other groups.  Mr. Backe pointed out that this was a given - that the FGDC will not duplicate existing standards efforts.  He also stated that since we do not know the exact overlap between our proposed standard and the Chemical Abstract Society Standard that we not limit ourselves in our proposal.  Mr. Ed Racht (USACE) recommended that we remember to coordinate with the Chemical Abstract Society as we pursue development of this standard.  We can always modify the proposal as we get further along in the project.  The proposal was approved by the Facilities Working Group and will be submitted to the Standards Working Group.  This signifies the intent to develop a standard. 
<LI>The TSSDS Environmental Hazards Entity will be expanded tremendously in version 1.6, due out in the 2 months.  Mr. Backe will provide a stripped down version of that for submittal to the Facilities Working Group as a draft Environmental Hazards Standard.  
<LI>ACTION: Submit the Proposal for a Environmental Hazards Data Content Standard to the Standards Working Group (Mr. M.K. Miles).   
</UL>

5) Geographic Army Reserve Information System (GARIS) Demo (Bill Gavazzi, USACE):
<UL>
<LI> Mr. Gavazzi demonstrated GARIS, which he developed to manage complex facility and environmental information at Army Reserve facilities.  GARIS operates in the Microstation, ORACLE, Windows NT environment and it also uses the TSSDS.  The Army Reserve has 10 Regional Support Commands (which correspond to the EPA and FEMA regions) with approximately 1400 facilities.  Mr. Gavazzi has established a process to accept the facility paper maps and drawings, rasterize and vectorize them, and import them into GARIS.  There were a lot of questions on GARIS for Mr. Gavazzi and comments that it would be nice to have more technology demos at our meetings. 
</UL> 

6)  Proposal for a Facility ID Data Standard (Bruce Bargmeyer, EPA):
<UL>
<LI>Mr. Bargmeyer presented a proposal for the development of a Facility ID Standard.  The group asked that he make several modifications and he has done this so quickly that the modified version is <A HREF="./07-15-96.attatch5.html">attached</A>.  There was a lot of discussion about the definition of facility, guidelines on a hierarchy of components, etc. and Ms Capps reminded the group that the proposal just signifies the intent to develop a standard, not that all the technical details have been worked out.  The group said that they would like a little more time to review the proposal before submitting to the Standards Working Group.  If Ms Capps does not receive comments by 2 August she will assume the Chair can submit this standard. 
<LI>Mr. Bargmeyer asked for volunteers to work on the proposal and Messrs Kevin Backe and Ron Niemi (USACE), Mr. Dan McHugh (NY City MTA), Ms Carolyn Davis (FEMA), and Ms Dee McFadden-Wallace (GSA) volunteered.  Ms Davis recommended that everyone get their existing ID Code information together in preparation for the first meeting. 
<LI>Mr. Joyce recommended that since we have made some progress on our pursuit of a Feature ID Standard we should get the FGDC Framework Project Manager to our next meeting. 
<LI>ACTION: Review  the Proposal for a Facility ID Data Standard and provide comments to Ms Capps by 2 August (Facilities Working Group). 
<LI>ACTION: If no comments are received by 2 August or comments received by 2 August are easily incorporated, submit the Proposal for a Facility ID Standard to the Standards Working Group (Mr. M.K. Miles).   
<LI>ACTION: Tell Mr. Bargmeyer if you volunteer to be on the project team to develop the standard and get your existing ID Code info together (Facilities Working Group). 
<LI>ACTION: Invite Mr. Mike Domaratz, FGDC Framework Manager, to the next meeting (Ms Penny Capps). 
</UL> 
 
7)   Next Meeting:
<UL>
	<LI>The next meeting will be 9 September from 1-4 in Room 8222D of the Pulaski Building, 20 Massachusetts Avenue, NW, Washington, DC.  
</UL> 
</BODY>
</HTML> 
