<title>Introducing Corning Besselaar</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
<meta name="FORMATTER" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>
<body background="images/backgrnd.gif">
<p align="center"><MAP NAME="FrontPageMap"><AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="1, 3, 103, 37" HREF="index.htm"></MAP><a href="/corningb/_vti_map/intro.htm.map"><img
align="bottom" src="images/home.gif" width="104" alt="Home Page"
ismap usemap="#FrontPageMap" height="38" border="0"></a></p>
<p align="center"><img src="images/logo.gif" align="bottom"
width="363" height="31"></p>
<p align="center"><em>A Corning Pharmaceutical Services Company</em></p>
<h1><u>Introducing Corning Besselaar...</u></h1>
<p>Corning Besselaar is the industry leader in clinical <a
href="ddc.htm">drug development </a>services for both the
pharmaceutical and biotechnology industries. To meet a clients
specific needs in the <a href="ddc.htm">drug development</a>
cycle, Corning Besselaar draws upon a world of resources around
the globe.</p>
<p>As part of the <a href="cps.htm">Corning Pharmaceutical
Services (CPS) </a>network, Corning Besselaar can bring together
the combined <a href="drugex.htm">experience</a> and <a
href="servic.htm">capabilities</a> of the world's leading drug
development companies in each stage of the Pharmaceutical and
Biotechnological development.</p>
<p>Corning Besselaar is the world's largest contract research
organisation (CRO) and provides a range of services to the
pharmaceutical industry, assisting in the conduct of the clinical
trials required in the approval procedure for new drugs using the<a
href="technol.htm"> latest technology.</a></p>
<p>The company provides assistance at all stages of the drug
development process, from early pre-approval trials involving
perhaps just 20 healthy volunteers in a hospital setting at the <a
href="phasei.htm">Corning Besselaar Clinical Research Unit </a>in
Leeds UK through to large scale peri-approval studies which may
involve thousands of patients handled by the <a
href="phaseiii.htm">Phase III</a> units and the<a href="edmc.htm">
European Data Management Centre (EDMC).</a> Corning Besselaar's
involvement may be limited to assisting in the monitoring of the
trials or in the preparing of<a href="regulato.htm"> regulatory</a>
documentation. But often it extends to providing a complete
service to a pharmaceutical company involving clinical
monitoring, provision of <a href="regulato.htm">regulatory</a>
and study planning advice and full data management, statistical
analysis and reporting of the results. Over the last 20 years the
company has performed work for clients on over 500 studies in a
broad spectrum of <a href="drugex.htm">therapeutic areas.</a></p>
<p>In providing <a href="ddc.htm">drug development</a> services,
Corning Bessselaar is able to draw upon its <a href="drugex.htm">extensive
experience</a> gained through it many years of operating.
Experience in conducting European and global studies according to <a
href="gcp.htm">GCP</a> as well as a proven track record of
adhering to strict timelines are important determinants in the
selection of a CRO. Corning Besselaar offers all of these
benefits.</p>
<p>Corning Besselaar is part of the <a href="cps.htm">Corning
Pharmaceutical Services</a> Family of companies, which are
committed to providing customer service with integrity and <a
href="iso9001.htm">quality</a>.</p>
<p>Corning Pharmaceutical Services has the vision of providing
the fastest <a href="ddc.htm">development</a> of new
pharmaceuticals with the aim of improving the quality of human
health worldwide.</p>
<p align="center"><MAP NAME="FrontPageMap1"><AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="354, 83, 449, 118" HREF="pact.htm"><AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="301, 158, 390, 193" HREF="edmc.htm"><AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="167, 157, 270, 209" HREF="regulato.htm"><AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="230, 82, 325, 121" HREF="phaseiii.htm"><AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="113, 84, 204, 117" HREF="phaseii.htm"><AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="42, 158, 162, 205" HREF="health.htm"><AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="1, 87, 83, 132" HREF="phasei.htm"><AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="301, 158, 390, 193" HREF="edmc.htm"><AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="167, 157, 270, 209" HREF="regulato.htm"><AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="230, 82, 325, 121" HREF="phaseiii.htm"><AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="113, 84, 204, 117" HREF="phaseii.htm"><AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="42, 158, 162, 205" HREF="health.htm"><AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="1, 87, 83, 132" HREF="phasei.htm"><AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="301, 158, 390, 193" HREF="edmc.htm"><AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="167, 157, 270, 209" HREF="regulato.htm"><AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="230, 82, 325, 121" HREF="phaseiii.htm"><AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="113, 84, 204, 117" HREF="phaseii.htm"><AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="42, 158, 162, 205" HREF="health.htm"><AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="1, 87, 83, 132" HREF="phasei.htm"></MAP><a href="/corningb/_vti_map/intro.htm.1.map"><img
align="bottom" src="images/structur.gif" width="450" ismap
usemap="#FrontPageMap1" height="213" border="0"></a></p>
<h2 align="center">Please <blink>click</blink> on the area of
interest on the map above</h2>
<hr>
<p align="center"><MAP NAME="FrontPageMap2"><AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="367, 5, 456, 106" HREF="library.htm"><AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="278, 7, 363, 103" HREF="cps.htm"><AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="187, 7, 272, 103" HREF="caropps.htm"><AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="97, 7, 182, 103" HREF="contact.htm"><AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="6, 7, 92, 103" HREF="index.htm"><AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="368, 7, 452, 103" HREF="http://sthomas.technocom.com/CBE2/library.htm"><AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="278, 7, 363, 103" HREF="cps.htm"><AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="187, 7, 272, 103" HREF="caropps.htm"><AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="97, 7, 182, 103" HREF="contact.htm"><AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="6, 7, 92, 103" HREF="index.htm"><AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="368, 7, 452, 103" HREF="http://sthomas.technocom.com/CBE2/library.htm"><AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="278, 7, 363, 103" HREF="cps.htm"><AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="187, 7, 272, 103" HREF="caropps.htm"><AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="97, 7, 182, 103" HREF="contact.htm"><AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="6, 7, 92, 103" HREF="index.htm"><AREA COORDS="0,0,10000,10000" HREF="index.htm"></MAP><a href="/corningb/_vti_map/intro.htm.2.map"><img
