<title>Regulatory Services</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
<meta name="FORMATTER" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>
<body background="images/backgrnd.gif">
<h1 align="center"><MAP NAME="FrontPageMap"><AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="2, 3, 103, 37" HREF="index.htm"></MAP><a href="/corningb/_vti_map/regulato.htm.map"><img
align="bottom" src="images/home.gif" width="104" alt="Home Page"
ismap usemap="#FrontPageMap" height="38" border="0"></a></h1>
<h1><u>European Regulatory Services</u></h1>
<p><u>REGULATORY AFFAIRS - EUROPE, BUSINESS CENTRE</u></p>
<p>The Corning Besselaar Regulatory Affairs Business Centre
assists client companies to obtain approvals from regulatory
agencies for human medicines, animal medicines and medical
devices so that these products are available for the public.</p>
<h3>European Regulatory Services</h3>
<p>The regulatory environment is ever evolving and the regulatory
challenges in Europe resulting from International Harmonisation,
new European Regulatory Procedures and associated legislation
have never been greater, but we provide our clients with
up-to-date knowledge of the current requirements and speed new
drugs to the market place.</p>
<p>Our regulatory specialists offer experience in developing
innovative regulatory strategies to expedite product development
and marketing approval in the pharmaceutical, veterinary and
device areas.</p>
<p>A successful development programme leads to maximal market
penetration in the shortest cycle time. Corning Besselaar and
Corning Hazleton have experience in identifying development
programmes to obtain marketing approval and in tackling the
various regulatory hurdles to speed new products to market in the
most time-efficient and cost-effective manner.</p>
<h3>Corning Besselaar and <a href="hazel.htm">Corning Hazleton</a>
can assist with:</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Strategic advice and constancy</li>
    <li>Preparation of regulatory documentation</li>
    <li>Submission of marketing authorisation applications and
        follow-up</li>
    <li>Regulatory authority liaison</li>
    <li>Co-ordination of clinical trial supplies</li>
    <li>Quality assurance and auditing</li>
    <li>Adverse event (AE) processing/reporting for clinical
        trials and marketed products and preparation of periodic
        safety updates</li>
    <li>World-wide regulatory expertise</li>
</ul>
<h3>World-wide Regulatory Experience</h3>
<p>We aim to provide the highest levels of quality and service
available anywhere in the industry and to help our clients to
achieve their regulatory target in the most time-efficient and
cost-effective way possible. Corning Besselaar and Corning
Hazleton have offices located across Europe, North America,
Australia and Japan. We provide services to support regulatory
requirements across Europe (EU and Central and Eastern Europe),
USA, Canada, Middle East, Africa, Australia, Asia, South America
and Japan.</p>
<h2><u>Experience in developing innovative regulatory strategies </u></h2>
<p>Our expertise in regulatory affairs was recognised by the
European Commission, who chose in 1992 Corning Besselaar in
partnership with Deloitte &amp; Touche to advise on the structure
and operations of the European Medicines Evaluation Agency (EMEA)
at Canary Wharf, London. The EMEA is responsible for
co-ordinating all activities associated with the new centralised
procedure and for co-ordinating adverse event reporting
(pharmacovigilance), GCP, GLP and GMP compliance throughout
Europe.</p>
<p>More recently, Corning Besselaar and Deloitte &amp; Touche
have undertaken a study for the National Drugs Advisory Board
(NDAB) on the recommended structure, systems and procedures for
the proposed Irish Medicines Board.</p>
<p>We work within a Total Quality Management System, which is
applied across all areas of work. The department responsible for
co-ordinating the preparation of regulatory documentation is
accredited to the <a href="iso9001.htm">BS EN ISO 9001</a>
international quality standard for preparation of regulatory
submissions.</p>
<p>Corning Besselaar Quality Assurance and auditing activities
encompass both the audits of investigator sites, clinical
research facilities, regulatory documents, databases and clinical
trial reports, and the process audits of activities in the
operational areas of Corning Besselaar.</p>
<p>Experienced staff with proven records in world-wide regulatory
procedures and strategies and our commitment to Total Quality
Management assures that we will exceed our clients every
expectation.</p>
