<head>
<title>ISO 9001</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
<meta name="FORMATTER" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>
<body background="images/backgrnd.gif">
<h2 align="center"><a href="index.htm"><img src="images/home.gif"
align="bottom" border="0" width="104" height="38"></a></h2>
<h2 align="center"><img src="images/logo.gif" align="bottom"
width="363" height="31"></h2>
<h2><a href="edmc.htm"><u>EDMC</u></a><u> CERTIFICATION TO BS EN
ISO 9001</u></h2>
<h2>At the beginning of February assessors from BSI QA
recommended <a href="edmc.htm">EDMC</a> for certification to <a
href="http://www.best.com/~iso9000/alt/ISOLinks.html">BS EN ISO
9001</a>, the internationally recognised quality systems
standard. This certification was sought to support EDMC's work to
GCP; one of the demands of GCP being that a quality management
system be in place.</h2>
<p>Any business, from the smallest to the largest, can apply to
register, whether it is a manufacturing or service industry.
Businesses can apply to register one area of their activities or
all of them. Within Corning Besselaar Europe, the <a
href="http://www.corningbesselaar.co.uk">Corning Besselaar
Clinical Research Unit </a>in Leeds gained its certificate in
1995, and is now to be followed by EDMC in 1996.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.best.com/~iso9000/alt/isolinks.html">BS EN
ISO 9001</a> does not impose a standardised bureaucratic system
on a company. In fact, it is not a single system at all, but is
unique to each user. The standard is simple common sense set down
in an organised way, seeking to define best working practices. <a
href="edmc.htm">EDMC</a> decides the best way to run its
business, not the standard or BSI QA. Then, by regular assessment
visits, BSI QA helps to ensure these best practice methods are
being maintained and improved upon.</p>
<p>BSI registered firms report a wide range of benefits . <a
href="http://www.best.com/~iso9000/alt/isolinks.html">BS EN ISO
9001</a> helps to make companies more competitive. Many
registered firms report a significant reduction of waste in both
time and materials. The quality system reduces the risk of
expensive mistakes and enables prompt, effective correction of
any defects. It also ensures a complete record of every activity
to resolve any disputes. Ultimately, pursuit of a policy of
continuous improvement results in more satisfied customers and
more repeat business. </p>
<p><img src="images/bsi.gif" align="bottom" width="80"
height="77"> Both the <a href="edmc.htm">European Data Management
Centre (EDMC)</a> and the <a
href="http://www.corningbesselaar.co.uk/">Corning Besselaar
Clinical Research Unit</a> are accredited to BS EN ISO 9001.</p>
<h2><a href="http://www.best.com/~iso9000/alt/isolinks.html"><u>More
Information</u></a></h2>
