<html>
<head>
<title>Corning PACT</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
<meta name="FORMATTER" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>
<body background="images/backgrnd.gif">
<p align="center"><MAP NAME="FrontPageMap"><AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="1, 2, 103, 37" HREF="INDEX.HTM"></MAP><a href="/corningb/_vti_map/pact.htm.map"><img
align="bottom" src="images/home.gif" width="104" ismap
usemap="#FrontPageMap" height="38" border="0"></a></p>
<p align="center"><img src="images/pactbig.gif" align="bottom"
width="326" height="30"></p>
<p>Corning PACT is the world's largest pharmaceutical research
services company dedicated to the design, organisation, conduct
and analysis of Phase IIIb and Phase IV &quot;periapproval&quot;
clinical research studies. </p>
<p>These studies bridge the gap between data derived from
registration (<a href="regulato.htm">regulatory approval</a>)
studies and information needs arising from actual medical
practice. They meet a variety of drug development objectives
including: (a) expanding safety and efficacy data, (b) evaluating
product utility and acceptability in targeted patient subgroups,
(c) reinforcing labelling or advertising claims, (d) collecting
quality-of -life and therapeutic cost data and (e) making novel
therapies available quickly to patients in need (compassionate
use programs). These studies are frequently comparative in design
and may involve several therapies. Corning PACT has conducted
over 70 of these studies, many multinational in scope, involving
more than 500,000 patients.</p>
<p>Currently Corning PACT is involved in two European programs on
behalf of two leading multinational pharmaceutical companies. The
first is a Safety Assessment of Marketed Medicines (SAMM) study
in the United Kingdom. This study is one of the first of its type
in Europe and will involve 2,500 General Practitioners and 20,000
patients. The second is a multinational expanded access program
involving a novel AIDS therapy. This program may have as many as
2,000 physicians and 10,000 patients enrolled throughout Europe,
North America, and Australia.</p>
<h3><a href="http://www.bio.com/home/corning/pact.html"><u>More
information</u></a></h3>
