<html>
<head>
<title>Phase II -Europe</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Vermeer FrontPage 1.0">
<meta name="FORMATTER" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>
<body background="images/backgrnd.gif">
<p align="center"><MAP NAME="FrontPageMap"><AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="3, 2, 103, 37" HREF="index.htm"></MAP><a href="/corningb/_vti_map/phaseii.htm.map"><img
align="bottom" src="images/home.gif" width="104" ismap
usemap="#FrontPageMap" height="38" border="0"></a></p>
<h1 align="center"><img src="images/logo.gif" align="bottom"
width="363" height="31"></h1>
<h1><u>PHASE II Europe</u></h1>
<p>In late 1994, the Phase II Europe Business Unit was
established to fill the perceived gap between the <a
href="phasei.htm">Phase I Clinic in Leeds</a> and the <a
href="PhaseIII.htm">Phase III</a> group providing the connection
between the two 'clinical phases'. With its objective of becoming
the first choice of pharmaceutical companies for European Phase
II services, the Phase II Europe Unit also set about to compete
for its own, stand-alone business.</p>
<p>Phase II trials are usually the first in which a drug is given
to a specific population of patients. Generally, Phase II studies
involve fewer patients than <a href="PhaseIII.htm">Phase III</a>
and also take less time. Phase II trials are usually the first in
which a drug is given to the patients for whom it is being
developed. These trials assess the drug's activity and short-term
safety, and they are important for determining optimal dose
ranges. Phase II studies typically involve fewer patients and
take less time than Phase III trials.</p>
<p>The Phase II Business Unit's main objective is to become the
first choice of pharmaceutical companies for European Phase II
services. In eighteen months the Phase II Unit has grown from one
person to sixteen with a projected growth by the end of 1996 to
nearly forty personnel. The Unit attracts clients not only with
reputation of <a href="intro.htm">Corning Besselaar</a> but also
with the experience and professionalism within the group and the
multi-lingual capabilities of its French, German and Italian
speakers.</p>
<p>With access to the <a href="hazel.htm">pre-clinical</a> and <a
href="phasei.htm">Phase I</a> results, the Phase II Unit speeds
the early development to completion and can produce a &quot;go/no
go&quot; decision within 12 months. Hence the term <a
href="fastrak.htm">&quot;fast-track&quot;.</a> Phase II Business
Unit aims to assist in the fast-track access for drugs from
pre-clinical studies through to safety and efficacy studies in
patients.</p>
<p>In order to provide the services customers expect of the unit,
close liaison with other Corning Besselaar groups such as <a
href="regulato.htm">Regulatory Affairs</a> and the Phase I Clinic
in Leeds is required.</p>
<p>At present, the Phase II Unit has fifteen ongoing and three
completed studies in therapeutic areas such as asthma and HIV.</p>
<hr>
