<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//W3O/DTD HTML//EN">

<html>
<head>
<title>Interactive Voice Response System - IVRS</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
<meta name="FORMATTER" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>
<body background="images/backgrnd.gif">
<h1 align="center"><u><MAP NAME="FrontPageMap"><AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="1, 3, 103, 37" HREF="index.htm"></MAP><a href="/corningb/_vti_map/ivrs.htm.map"><img
align="bottom" src="images/home.gif" width="104" ismap
usemap="#FrontPageMap" height="38" border="0"></a></u></h1>
<h1><u>IVRS: Interactive Voice Response System</u></h1>
<p>The IVRS is a computer system which uses a standard touch-tone
telephone to manage &quot;just-in-time&quot; clinical trial drug
supplies. IVRS has been shown to dramatically reduce drug wastage
during clinical trials by dynamically assigning study medication
to patients. Investigators communicate with IVRS using the key
pad on a touch-tone telephone. The IVRS responds using digitized
human voice.</p>
<h2>Key advantages of Corning Besselaar's IVRS System</h2>
<ul>
    <li>Offers centralized data collection.</li>
    <li>&quot;just-in-time&quot; management of clinical drug
        supplies.</li>
    <li>Low equipment overhead in the field.</li>
    <li>Multi-lingual and multinational access.</li>
    <li>Simple interface.</li>
    <li>IVRS Assists in Drug Supply Management</li>
</ul>
<p>Each box of drug is numbered uniquely, independent of patient
numbers. A pharmacist or study coordinator calls the IVRS each
time the patient receives drug. Boxes of drug are dynamically
matched to the patient at the moment of assignment.</p>
<p>With an IVRS system only a small start-up supply of drug is
sent to each site. If a patient drops out of the study, no
additional drug supplies are lost. Study sites are resupplied
with drug in a just-in time fashion based on their actual and
projected drug usage. Significant drug savings may be achieved
and clinical trials may begin with minimal supplies while
additional drug is being manufactured. Matching drug to patient
at the moment of assignment allows for pooling of drug supplies
across study protocols.The IVRS also makes real-time enrollment
and visit schedule information available to sponsors while
pharmacists and researchers remain blinded. </p>
<h3>IVRS Assists Dynamic Patient Randomization</h3>
<p>Odds of assignment to a treatment arm are based on information
not available before the trial begins. The most common adjustment
uses treatment counts across sites to adjust treatment
assignments within sites. The balance may be adjusted strictly
within treatment or by overall counts of other stratifying
variables (sex, age, disease progression, etc.)</p>
<h3>IVRS can be used for Study Patient Diaries</h3>
<p>The IVRS is also useful for study patient diaries. New
patients are registered by study coordinators and trained to use
the IVRS for keeping their diaries with the pertinent information
recorded in real time. The IVRS provides automatic reminders if
the patient is late entering data. </p>
<hr>
<p align="center"><MAP NAME="FrontPageMap1"><AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="459, 7, 543, 103" HREF="http://sthomas.technocom.com/CBE2/library.htm"><AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="368, 7, 452, 103" HREF="http://sthomas.technocom.com/CBE2/library.htm"><AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="278, 7, 363, 103" HREF="cps.htm"><AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="187, 7, 272, 103" HREF="caropps.htm"><AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="97, 7, 182, 103" HREF="contact.htm"><AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="6, 7, 92, 103" HREF="index.htm"><AREA COORDS="0,0,10000,10000" HREF="index.htm"></MAP><a href="/corningb/_vti_map/ivrs.htm.1.map"><img
align="bottom" src="images/buttons.gif" width="550"
alt="Click here to get back to the Home Page!" ismap
usemap="#FrontPageMap1" height="110" border="0"></a></p>
