ismap usemap="#FrontPageMap" height="38" border="0"></a></h1>
<h1 align="center"><img src="images/logo.gif" align="bottom"
width="363" height="31"></h1>
<h1><strong><u>Phase II and III </u></strong></h1>
<ul>
    <li><a href="#Clinical Research Managers"><strong>Clinical
        Research Managers (Phase III)</strong></a></li>
    <li><a href="#Principal CRAs"><strong>Principal Clinical
        Research Associates (Phases II and III)</strong></a></li>
    <li><a href="#Senior CRAs"><strong>Senior Clinical Research
        Associates (Phases II and III)</strong></a></li>
    <li><a href="#CRAs"><strong>Clinical Research Associates
        (Phase III)</strong></a></li>
</ul>
<p><a name="Clinical Research Managers"><em><strong>Clinical
Research Managers</strong></em></a> will have at least 7 years
relevant clinical research experience in a pharmaceutical company
or CRO, together with previous line management responsibility.
You will act as Project Manager/Project Director for one or more
designated global projects and will have full line management
responsibility for the recruitment and development of clinical
and administrative staff.</p>
<p><a name="Principal CRAs"><em><strong>Principal CRAs</strong></em></a>
will have at least five years relevant clinical research
experience (including project management responsibility).
Ideally, you will have worked on pan-European projects and
possess excellent communication and leadership skills. You will
be responsible for all aspects of clinical research from protocol
design, managing budgets and for the right candidates, line
management responsibilities and the development and training of
staff. You will enjoy considerable autonomy in planning work
schedules and inspiring effective teamwork from your colleagues.</p>
<p><a name="Senior CRAs"><em><strong>Senior CRAs</strong></em></a>
will have at least three years relevant clinical research
experience. Ideally you will have experience of project
co-ordination. You will be involved with all aspects of clinical
research from writing protocols to monitoring studies and
dependent on experience, may gain project management
responsibility.</p>
<p><a name="CRAs"><em><strong>CRAs</strong></em></a> will have at
least 12 months site monitoring experience within a
pharmaceutical company or CRO. Although the role will be
principally involved with monitoring, you will also assist with
the recruitment of investigators.</p>
<p>All these posts require a minimum of a life sciences degree or
a nursing qualification. Candidates interested in joining Phase
II must be prepared to travel to Europe. In return, we offer a
competitive salary and first class benefits package which
includes car, bonus, non-contributory pension scheme and free
medical insurance (after a short qualifying period).</p>
<p>&#160;If you are interested in joining our rapidly expanding
organisation, please forward your Curriculum Vitae to:</p>
