<html>
<head>
<title>Opportunities in Clinical Data Management</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
<meta name="FORMATTER" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>
<body background="images/backgrnd.gif">
<p align="center"><MAP NAME="FrontPageMap"><AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="2, 0, 103, 37" HREF="index.htm"></MAP><a href="/corningb/_vti_map/opportun.htm.map"><img
align="bottom" src="images/home.gif" width="104" alt="Home Page"
ismap usemap="#FrontPageMap" height="38" border="0"></a></p>
<h1><u>Opportunities in Clinical Data Management</u></h1>
<p>Clinical<a href="edmc.htm"> Data Management</a> are
responsible for managing the data from international clinical
trials. This involves setting up databases, clarifying and
reviewing case report forms, running diagnostic programs, raising
queries and editing the database. At the more senior levels, you
will be the main point of contact for the client and will have
project and line management responsibilities.</p>
<p>You will have the chance to gain experience in international
projects covering a variety of therapeutic areas and no matter
what level you are at, you will have plenty of opportunity to
make a significant contribution to the success of the department.</p>
<p>We require nursing qualifications or a life sciences degree as
a minimum qualification for each position, with previous relevant
experience for the more senior positions</p>
<h2><u>Clinical Data Management / Statisticians / Statistical
Programmers</u></h2>
<p><a href="intro.htm">Corning Besselaar</a> can offer you the
chance to gain supervisory responsibility, along with the
opportunity to work on your own initiative and take on more and
more responsibility as you progress up our career ladder.</p>
<p>For more senior candidates within Statistics, Statistical
Programming and Clinical Data Management, you will have a key
management role within the department. You will be involved in
the management of multi-disciplinary projects across EDMC,
including project budget and timeline control, resource planning,
client meetings and line management.</p>
<p>Candidates for all the positions will be computer literate,
self starters, accurate and have excellent communication skills.
The individuals must have the ability to work effectively in a
team and to tight deadlines, promoting the highest professional
standards, even when under pressure. A clear appreciation of the
requirements of our clients is required, together with a
pro-active approach to any problems.</p>
<h3><u>Statisticians</u></h3>
<p>Statisticians provide statistical input into clinical trial
protocols, preparation of statistical analysis plans, and the
analysis and reporting of clinical trials. At senior levels, they
provide statistical consultancy relating to all aspects of the
clinical development process and also represent the statistics
department at high level meetings with our clients.</p>
<p>Candidates will have an MSc in Medical Statistics (or
equivalent). </p>
<h3><u>Statistical Programmers</u> </h3>
<p>Statistical Programmers provide SAS programming support to
data management and statistical activities. Their work involves
input into database design, development of program
specifications, diagnostic programming and development of
programs for data presentations. In addition, they are
responsible for providing our clients with copies of our clinical
trial databases to meet their specifications.</p>
<p>Candidates may have a background in mathematics, statistics,
computing or life sciences, but SAS skills are essential. </p>
<p>If you are interested in joining our rapidly expanding
organisation, please forward your Curriculum Vitae to:</p>
<dl>
    <dd>Amy Hulme </dd>
    <dd>Human Resources Department</dd>
    <dd>Corning Besselaar Limited</dd>
    <dd>7 Roxborough Way</dd>
    <dd>Maidenhead, Berkshire SL6 3UD</dd>
    <dd>United Kingdom.
        <p>e-mail: <a href="mailto:sthomas@corningb.co.uk">sthomas@corningb.co.uk</a></p>
        <p><strong>Please mark applications: INTERNET</strong></p>
    </dd>
</dl>
