<title>Information services</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
<meta name="FORMATTER" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>
<body background="images/backgrnd.gif">
<p align="center"><MAP NAME="FrontPageMap"><AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="3, 2, 103, 37" HREF="index.htm"></MAP><a href="/corningb/_vti_map/infoser.htm.map"><img
align="bottom" src="images/home.gif" width="104" alt="Home Page"
ismap usemap="#FrontPageMap" height="38" border="0"></a></p>
<p align="center"><img src="images/logo.gif" align="bottom"
width="363" height="31"></p>
<h1><u>Information Services Europe</u></h1>
<p>The Information Services group's mission is to provide <a
href="intro.htm">Corning Besselaar Europe </a>with the
technology, support and training so as to enable us to provide
outstanding services to our clients.</p>
<p>We have an extensive WAN/LAN structure and work closely with
our sister companies in <a href="cps.htm">Corning Pharmaceutical
Services </a>in Europe and the US. Our technical architecture is
based on client/server technology.</p>
<p>We use Sybase, Oracle on HP Unix machines and Powerbuilder for
client applications. We have a fast growing and extensive Lotus
Notes&#174; capability. We also use the desktop suite MS Office,
MS Project and other applications when required.</p>
<p>The IS department also conducts all internal IT training for
Corning Besselaar within the United Kingdom and in other European
Countries.</p>
<h4><u>&#160;Senior Analyst Programmer</u></h4>
<p>The information services department requires an analyst
programmer to develop, integrate, enhance and support the
European corporate systems that provide financial, project and
human resource information.</p>
<p>Working as part of the Applications Group, the ideal candidate
will need to have a good knowledge of Powerbuilder and Sybase
with a full understanding of implementing client server
applications over LAN and WAN. Some experience of developing and
supporting financial reporting systems within a clinical
environment would be distinct advantage.</p>
<p>In addition to these technical skills the successful applicant
will have strong communication and organisational skills and be
able to supply evidence of successful delivery of client server
applications under pressure to tight deadlines.</p>
<h4><u>Analyst Programmer</u></h4>
<p>We also require an Analyst Programmer to support the European
corporate data management systems based on Paradox and also
develop, integrate and support new replacement system that will
give the company a clear business advantage.</p>
<p>Working as part of the Applications Group, the ideal candidate
will need to have a mixture of Paradox, Powerbuilder and Sybase
technical skills coupled with strong communication and
organisational skills and have evidence of successful delivery of
client server applications under pressure to tight deadlines. A
knowledge of MS Access and clinical data management processes
would be advantage.</p>
<p>&#160;</p>
<p>If you are interested in joining our rapidly expanding
organisation, please forward your Curriculum Vitae to:</p>
<dl>
    <dd>Amy Hulme </dd>
    <dd>Human Resources Department</dd>
    <dd>Corning Besselaar Limited</dd>
    <dd>7 Roxborough Way</dd>
    <dd>Maidenhead, Berkshire SL6 3UD</dd>
    <dd>United Kingdom.</dd>
    <dd>&#160;</dd>
    <dd>Or e-mail <a href="mailto:sthomas@corningb.co.uk">sthomas@corningb.co.uk</a></dd>
    <dd>&#160;</dd>
    <dd>Please mark all applications <strong>INTERNET</strong></dd>
</dl>
