width="363" height="31"></p>
<h1 align="left"><u>General Career Opportunities</u></h1>
<p>The following vacancies have arisen within our Maidenhead
Office:</p>
<ul>
    <li><a href="#European Accounting Manager">European
        Accounting Manager</a></li>
</ul>
<h3><a name="European Accounting Manager"><u>European Accounting
Manager</u></a></h3>
<p>The main responsibilities for this position will be to ensure
monthly group financial reporting deadlines are met by Covance
Clinical Europe and to ensure audits are conducted efficiently
and that the financial statements are filed on time. You will
also ensure statutory filing deadlines are met. In addition to
this you will be required to prepare financial statements for the
Irish and UK Company. Other responsibilities will be to ensure
that tax returns are submitted on time and quarterly and yearly
group reporting requirements for accounting and tax are met on
time. It will be your responsibility to actively manage and
organise the financial accounting group. You will also maintain
and install adequate internal controls, liaise with the group
internal auditors and prepare for and follow-up after audit
visits. In addition to this you will provide ad-hoc business
information to the US group head office and local management.</p>
<p>Secondary responsibilities will involve identifying and
implementing process improvement, update financial policies &amp;
procedures of CBE. Also to organise and implement the accounting
and procedural requirements for new offices around Europe. In
addition to this you will perform ad-hoc tasks as stipulated by
local or Head Office management.</p>
<p>The ideal candidate be a newly or recently qualified ACA with
first-time passes from a top 6 firm of chartered accountants. You
will have proven ability to meet tight deadlines and handle
multiple priorities. You will also possess excellent IT and
technical accounting skills. In addition to this you will have
the ability to communicate with all levels of the organisation's
employees. Languages, particularly German and French would be an
advantage and also exposure to the accounting requirements of
other European countries.</p>
<p>&#160;</p>
<p>If you are interested in joining our rapidly expanding
organisation, please forward your Curriculum Vitae to:</p>
<dl>
    <dd>Amy Hulme </dd>
    <dd>Human Resources Department</dd>
    <dd>Corning Besselaar Limited</dd>
    <dd>7 Roxborough Way</dd>
    <dd>Maidenhead, Berkshire SL6 3UD</dd>
    <dd>United Kingdom.</dd>
    <dd>&#160;</dd>
    <dd>Or e-mail <a href="mailto:sthomas@corningb.co.uk">sthomas@corningb.co.uk</a></dd>
    <dd>&#160;</dd>
    <dd>Please mark all applications <strong>INTERNET</strong></dd>
</dl>
