<head>
<title>CANDAs Computed Assisted Submissions</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
<meta name="FORMATTER" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>
<body background="images/backgrnd.gif">
<p align="center"><MAP NAME="FrontPageMap"><AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="3, 1, 103, 36" HREF="index.htm"></MAP><a href="/corningb/_vti_map/canda.htm.map"><img
align="bottom" src="images/home.gif" width="104" ismap
usemap="#FrontPageMap" height="38" border="0"></a></p>
<p align="center"><img src="images/logo.gif" align="bottom"
width="363" height="31"></p>
<h1><u>CANDAs/CAPLAs</u></h1>
<h1><u>Computer Assisted Submissions</u></h1>
<p><a href="intro.htm">Corning Besselaar</a>'s first CANDA was
prepared in 1987, making our organization a pioneer in computer
assisted development of NDAs. Corning Besselaar's CANDAs have
been well-received by the FDA with 8 completed submissions and a
permanent link established with the FDA for electronic mail.</p>
<h3>Key Advantages of Corning Besselaar's CANDA/CAPLA:</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Corning Besselaar utilizes a flexible design for the core
        CANDA, which is easily adaptable to the specific needs of
        each FDA reviewer.</li>
    <li>A hypertext environment allows the reviewer to
        &quot;point and click&quot; to create a path through the
        document following a particular train of thought.</li>
    <li>Menu selections, data queries, reports and special
        functions are tailored to facilitate review.</li>
    <li>Lotus Notes&#174; compatible.</li>
    <li>Scanned CRFs for patients who have dropped out or who
        have serious adverse events.</li>
    <li>Individual patient data retrieval.</li>
    <li>Retrieval of aggregate data across all patients.</li>
    <li>SAS programs can be run against relevant SAS data sets.
        Macros allow statistical reviewer easy access to SAS data
        sets. An integrated sub-setting feature is provided.</li>
</ul>
<h3>Services Corning Besselaar provides to develop a CANDA/CAPLA:</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Translation of data into relational database.</li>
    <li>Creation of interactive query screens and procedures.</li>
    <li>Testing/custom designing of the system:</li>
    <li>Integration of documents in hypertext format</li>
    <li>Scanning of CRFs</li>
    <li>Conversion of SAS programs to CANDA systems - exporting
        data to additional software packages</li>
    <li>Installation of the system at the FDA.</li>
    <li>Training.</li>
    <li>Continued support of FDA review.</li>
</ul>
<p><a href="intro.htm">Corning Besselaar</a> has provided an
average of two CANDAs per year over the past four years. As
technology continues to evolve, <a href="intro.htm">Corning
Besselaar</a> has the ability to customize and incorporate the
latest hardware and software features to accommodate both sponsor
and FDA reviewer.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.fda.gov/"><u>More Information on the FDA</u></a></p>
