<head>
<title>Fast Track Drug Development</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
<meta name="FORMATTER" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>
<body background="images/backgrnd.gif">
<h2 align="center"><MAP NAME="FrontPageMap"><AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="2, 3, 103, 37" HREF="index.htm"></MAP><a href="/corningb/_vti_map/fastrak.htm.map"><img
align="bottom" src="images/home.gif" width="104" ismap
usemap="#FrontPageMap" height="38" border="0"></a></h2>
<h2><u>Fast Track </u><a href="drugex.htm"><u>Drug Development</u></a></h2>
<p>This is the ability of <a href="cps.htm">Corning
Pharmaceutical Services</a> to help clients take a compound
through development (preclinical through Phase I and II) in a
quick, efficient and cost effective manner. In some cases, the
client can expect a go/no go decision within six months.</p>
<p>This process speeds drugs safely and efficiently through the <a
href="ddc.htm">drug development cycle</a> and assists in bringing
drugs to market in highly competitive fields. Using the fast
track strategy CPS can provide quality products by using multiple <a
href="cps.htm">CPS</a> units to achieve a common goal.</p>
<h2 align="center"><img src="images/fasttrak.gif" align="bottom"
width="250" height="251"></h2>
<h2><u>The Development Group: Your Path to Success</u></h2>
<p>Corning Besselaar<a href="phaseii.htm"> Phase II Europe</a>
provides what no other CRO offers; continuity from pre-clinical,
through Phase I to Phase II. Drug development experts from
Corning Hazleton Europe; the Corning Besselaar <a
href="phasei.htm">Phase I Unit in Leeds</a>, UK; the <a
href="phaseiii.htm">Phase III </a>Department; and the <a
href="regulato.htm">Regulatory</a> Department together with the
Phase II Unit comprise our unique Pharmaceutical Development
Co-ordination Group (PDCG). This Development Group is responsible
for managing pre-clinical, Phase I and Phase II study development
strategies to help create a seamless transition to Phase III.</p>
<p>The PDCG formulates pharmaceutical development strategies;
maintains a complete awareness of commercial positions and
development needs in the pharmaceutical industry; and reviews new
developments, techniques, and service capabilities.</p>
<p>Since the PDCG builds on the &quot;fast track&quot; concept -
speeding the clients drug from pre-clinical to the end of Phase
II studies, linkage of the Phase II Unit with PDCG translates
into faster, more successful, and less costly Phase II studies.</p>
<h2><a href="casestud.htm">Case Study</a></h2>
<hr>
<p align="center"><MAP NAME="FrontPageMap1"><AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="367, 5, 457, 107" HREF="library.htm"><AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="278, 7, 363, 103" HREF="cps.htm"><AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="187, 7, 272, 103" HREF="caropps.htm"><AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="97, 7, 182, 103" HREF="contact.htm"><AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="6, 7, 92, 103" HREF="index.htm"><AREA COORDS="0,0,10000,10000" HREF="index.htm"></MAP><a href="/corningb/_vti_map/fastrak.htm.1.map"><img
align="bottom" src="images/buttons.gif" width="460"
alt="Click here to get back to the Home Page!" ismap
usemap="#FrontPageMap1" height="110" border="0"></a></p>
