<html>
<head>
<title>Case Study</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
<meta name="FORMATTER" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>
<body background="images/backgrnd.gif">
<p align="center"><MAP NAME="FrontPageMap"><AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="3, 2, 103, 37" HREF="index.htm"><AREA COORDS="0,0,10000,10000" HREF="index.htm"></MAP><a href="/corningb/_vti_map/casestud.htm.map"><img
align="bottom" src="images/home.gif" width="104" alt="Home Page"
ismap usemap="#FrontPageMap" height="38" border="0"></a></p>
<h1>Case Study:</h1>
<h2><u>Speeding a Protease Inhibitor through the &quot;Fast Track</u>&quot;</h2>
<p>Both large and small pharmaceutical manufacturers are
utilising Corning Besselaar Europe for &quot;fast-track&quot;,
low-cost <a href="ddc.htm">drug development</a> and the
advantages of the world-wide <a href="cps.htm">Corning
Pharmaceutical Services (CPS)</a> network. For example, a
US-based, high-tech pharmaceutical company outsourced their
protease inhibitor to Corning Besselaar Europe to speed
development and reached a &quot;go/no-go&quot; decision within 12
months.</p>
<p>This client began development of its compound at the <a
href="hazel.htm">Corning Hazleton</a> facility, where
pre-clinical and animal toxicity studies were performed. Phase I
studies were successfully completed at <a href="phasei.htm">Corning
Besselaar, Leeds, UK</a>. Having come so far so quickly on the
CPS &quot;fast track,&quot; they naturally chose the <a
href="phaseii.htm">Corning Besselaar Phase II Unit</a> for
completion of the Phase II studies.</p>
<p>The initial pilot Phase II study and escalating dose study on
HIV-positive patients were both performed by the<a
href="phaseii.htm"> Corning Besselaar Phase II Europe</a> group
in Maidenhead, UK. The client continued to utilise the CPS
network for routine patient laboratory tests, assays on
haematology, and blood chemistries by outsourcing to <a
href="http://www.bio.com/home/corning/companies.html">Corning
SciCor</a> in Geneva. Additionally, the pharmacokinetic analysis
of samples was assayed by <a href="hazel.htm">Corning Hazleton </a>in
Harrogate, UK. </p>
<p>By outsourcing its development to Corning Besselaar Europe,
the client met the necessary regulatory requirements and
successfully completed the Phase II studies on their compound
without filing a costly IND. For this emerging drug company, the
CPS &quot;fast-track&quot; meant a &quot;go/no-go&quot; decision
in less than 12 months from pre-clinical through Phase II
development instead of an 18 - 24 months development timeline
with most other CROs.</p>
<hr>
