<title>Process Validation:Introduction</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
<meta name="FORMATTER" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>
<body background="images/backgrnd.gif" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"
link="#000080">
<h4 align="center"><MAP NAME="FrontPageMap"><AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="3, 0, 103, 37" HREF="INDEX.HTM"></MAP><a href="/corningb/_vti_map/procval1.htm.map"><img
align="bottom" src="IMAGES/home.gif" width="104" ismap
usemap="#FrontPageMap" height="38" border="0"></a></h4>
<h4 align="center"><img src="images/cps2.gif" align="bottom"
width="306" height="45"></h4>
<p>&#160; </p>
<h4>A Guide to Process Validation for Pharmaceuticals Produced in
Mammalian Cell Culture </h4>
<h1><u>Introduction </u></h1>
<p>This document is designed to provide an introduction to the
issues to be considered when planning a process validation for a
pharmaceutical produced in mammalian cell culture and intended
for use in man. It serves to demonstrate the approach and thought
processes involved in designing a study for the validation of
each stage of a purification process for the removal or
inactivation of virus. This is a general discussion, and the
exact validation programme for a specific product will need to be
established following detailed discussion between Corning
Hazleton and the client. </p>
<p>Before beginning a process validation it is necessary to have
thought about, and acted upon, a number of key issues. These are
dealt with as they arise under the relevant sections. </p>
<p>&#160;</p>
<table width="100%">
    <tr>
        <td width="50%"> 
        <p align="right"><img src="IMAGES/th_up.gif"
        align="bottom" width="25" height="19"> <a
        href="procindx.htm">Return to Contents</a> </p>
        </td>
        <td width="50%"> 
        <p align="left"><img src="IMAGES/r_hand.gif"
        align="bottom" width="33" height="14"> <a
        href="procval2.htm">Next page</a></p>
        </td>
    </tr>
</table>
