<title>Process Validation:Hazleton service</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
<meta name="FORMATTER" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>
<body background="images/backgrnd.gif" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"
link="#000080">
<h4 align="center"><img src="IMAGES/home.gif" align="bottom"
width="104" height="38"></h4>
<h4>A Guide to Process Validation for Pharmaceuticals Produced in
Mammalian Cell Culture </h4>
<p><img src="IMAGES/HAZELBG2.GIF" align="bottom" width="360"
height="30"></p>
<h1>Process Validation Service </h1>
<p>The information given in this document is, of necessity,
general in outline. Initially, a period of extensive consultation
with clients is required to advise on the planning of all aspects
of the experiments. We have found this to be a very valuable
preliminary to practical work which saves much time and effort in
the long run. </p>
<p>The validation itself usually involves personnel from the
manufacturing company running the scaled down process at<a
href="HAZEL.HTM"> Corning Hazleton</a>. Corning Hazleton provide
a controlled temperature laboratory for exclusive use, plus all
the staff required to provide load buffer spiked with high titre
virus and to accept and assay samples as they are generated by
the purification step. The purification is performed to GMP,
normally by the manufacturer, all other aspects of the work are
carried out by Corning Hazleton staff to GLP. Corning Hazleton
can, if desirable, carry out the whole process on behalf of the
client. We recommend that each stage is validated in duplicate. </p>
<p>We have available a range of high titre virus stocks prepared
in serum-free medium, and have much experience of performing
accurate and reliable plaque and focus-forming assays for their
detection. During the running of a validation a large excess of
cultures of indicator cells are provided to enable unforseen
circumstances to be accommodated, and Corning Hazleton staff are
available 24 hours a day if required. </p>
<p>During the study we fax results to clients as soon as they
become available, and complete, in-depth, draft and fully audited
final reports (one for each virus studied if required) will be
provided at the end of the study. </p>
