<html>
<head>
<title>Process Validation:Appendix 3</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
<meta name="FORMATTER" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>
<body background="images/backgrnd.gif" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"
link="#000080">
<h4 align="center"><MAP NAME="FrontPageMap"><AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="1, 0, 103, 37" HREF="INDEX.HTM"></MAP><a href="/corningb/_vti_map/procva10.htm.map"><img
align="bottom" src="IMAGES/home.gif" width="104" ismap
usemap="#FrontPageMap" height="38" border="0"></a></h4>
<h4 align="center"><img src="images/cps2.gif" align="bottom"
width="306" height="45"></h4>
<h4>A Guide to Process Validation for Pharmaceuticals Produced in
Mammalian Cell Culture </h4>
<h1>APPENDIX 3 </h1>
<h2>Example of an initial screening study for an inactivation
treatment </h2>
<h4>Effect of formaldehyde on poliovirus </h4>
<p>A stock of poliovirus at 7.5 x 107 plaque forming units
(pfu)/ml was treated with formaldehyde solution at 100&#181;g/ml
at two temperatures, in the presence and absence of added
protein. At various time points an aliquot was removed and the
residual titre determined by plaque assay. </p>
<table border="1" width="100%">
    <tr>
        <td> 
        <h4 align="center">Treatment time </h4>
        </td>
        <td> 
        <h4 align="center">No added protein at 37C (pfu/ml) </h4>
        </td>
        <td> 
        <h4 align="center">2 mg/ml BSA at<br>
        37C (pfu/ml) </h4>
        </td>
        <td> 
        <h4 align="center">No added protein at 4C (pfu/ml) </h4>
        </td>
        <td> 
        <h4 align="center">2 mg/ml BSA at<br>
        4C (pfu/ml) </h4>
        </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td>0 Hours</td>
        <td>7.5 x 10E7</td>
        <td>7.5 x 10E7</td>
        <td>7.5 x 10E7</td>
        <td>7.5 x 10E7</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td>1 Hour</td>
        <td>1.35 x 10E5</td>
        <td>2.1 x 10E5</td>
        <td>4.5 x 10E5</td>
        <td>4.5 x 10E5</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td>5 Hours</td>
        <td>5.0 x 10E3</td>
        <td>2.5 x 104</td>
        <td>6.0 x 10E5</td>
        <td>7.5 x 10E5</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td>3 Days</td>
        <td>0</td>
        <td>0</td>
        <td>2.6 x 10E3</td>
        <td>3.6 x 10E4</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td>7 Days</td>
        <td>0</td>
        <td>0</td>
        <td>1.0 x 10E2</td>
        <td>9.5 x 10E3</td>
    </tr>
</table>
<p>&#160; </p>
<h4>Conclusion </h4>
<p>As expected, virus kill is accomplished more rapidly at higher
temperature, and at low temperature the addition of protein has
some protective effect. </p>
<h3>END OF DOCUMENT </h3>
