<p align="center"><img src="IMAGES/HAZELBG2.GIF" align="bottom"
width="360" height="30"></p>
<h1 align="center">Better Answers to Old Questions: </h1>
<h1>New Applications of Analytical Techniques to Pharmaceutical
Safety Assessment.</h1>
<p>&#160;</p>
<p>A free seminar sponsored by <img src="IMAGES/hazelton.gif"
align="bottom" width="159" height="13"> </p>
<p><strong>October 15 1996</strong></p>
<p><strong>8:30am - 3:30pm</strong></p>
<p><strong>at the Princeton Marriott </strong></p>
<p><strong>Princeton, New Jersey</strong></p>
<p align="center"><u>Chairpersons: Joan Rener, Ph.D. Steve
Haworth, Ph.D.</u></p>
<h2><u>Seminar Topics</u></h2>
<p><strong><u>OVERVIEW</u></strong></p>
<ul>
    <li><em>Overview of Pharmaceutical Safety Assessment</em> -
        Joan Rener, Ph.D.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong><u>IN VITRO ANALYSIS</u></strong></p>
<ul>
    <li><em>Post- Translational Labelling of DNA addicts</em> -
        Vejay Reddy, Ph.D</li>
    <li><em>Gene Transfection</em> - Maria Cifone, Ph.D.</li>
    <li><em>Syrian Hamster Embryonic cell assay for Mutagenesis</em>
        - Roger Brauniger, B.S</li>
</ul>
<p><strong><u>ANALYTICAL CHEMISTRY</u></strong></p>
<ul>
    <li><em>Capillary Electrophoresis</em> - Craig Goldensoph,
        B.S</li>
    <li><em>Development of &quot;Generic&quot; Immunoassays for
        Human and Animal Species</em> - John Leete, Ph.D</li>
    <li><em>Flow Cytometric Analysis of T and B cell subsets</em>
        - Michael Neisler, Ph.D/ J. Waxdal, Ph.D.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong><u>ANIMAL MODELS</u></strong></p>
<ul>
    <li><em>Knockout, Muta and Onco Mice</em> - Brain Myhr, Ph.D.</li>
    <li><em>Advances in Infusion Technology in Laboratory Animals</em>
        - Mark Walker, D.V.M</li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h3>If you require further information. Please contact Doreen
Burton at Corning Hazleton. phone number 608-242-2712 extension
7992. </h3>
<hr>
<p>&#160;</p>
