<title>Quality Assurance Career Opportunities</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
<meta name="FORMATTER" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>
<body background="images/backgrnd.gif" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"
link="#000080">
<p align="center"><img src="IMAGES/home.gif" align="bottom"
width="104" height="38"></p>
<p align="center"><img src="IMAGES/LOGO.GIF" align="bottom"
width="363" height="31"><br>
<br>
<strong><u>QUALITY ASSURANCE AND TRAINING OFFICER </u></strong><br>
(full time 6 month temporary)<br>
<br>
<br>
Due to the continued secondment of a member of QATU staff a
temporary 6 month position, with a possibility of renewal, has
arisen within the Quality Assurance &amp; Training Unit (QATU)</p>
<p>Reporting to the Supervisor, QATU you will have responsibility
for managing the auditing programmes of specifically assigned
projects and any other non-project related auditing activities.</p>
<p>Further responsibilities will include reviewing Standard
Operating Procedures for all aspects of Quality Assurance, Good
Clinical Practice (GCP), Quality and Company Induction Training.</p>
<p>To apply for this position you must be educated to degree
level or equivalent in a scientific discipline with at least 1
years experience in a clinical research environment. Essential
for this position will be the ability to communicate and
negotiate effectively. Whilst utilising your skills, knowledge
and experience in order to consistently meet the high standards
required of a Quality Assurance &amp; Training Officer.</p>
<p>If you are interested in joining our rapidly expanding
organisation, please forward your Curriculum Vitae to:</p>
<dl>
    <dd>Amy Hulme </dd>
    <dd>Human Resources Department</dd>
    <dd>Corning Besselaar Limited</dd>
    <dd>7 Roxborough Way</dd>
    <dd>Maidenhead, Berkshire SL6 3UD</dd>
    <dd>United Kingdom.</dd>
    <dd>&#160;</dd>
    <dd>or contact: <a href="mailto:sthomas@corningb.co.uk">sthomas@corningb.co.uk</a></dd>
</dl>
<hr>
