<html>
<head>
<title>Corning Besselaar - Phase III</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
<meta name="FORMATTER" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>
<body background="images/backgrnd.gif">
<p align="center"><MAP NAME="FrontPageMap"><AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="4, 2, 103, 37" HREF="index.htm"></MAP><a href="/corningb/_vti_map/phaseiii.htm.map"><img
align="bottom" src="images/home.gif" width="104" ismap
usemap="#FrontPageMap" height="38" border="0"></a></p>
<h1 align="center"><img src="images/logo.gif" align="bottom"
width="363" height="31"></h1>
<h1>World Class Outsourced Clinical Research</h1>
<p>Corning Besselaar understands the problems faced in performing
clinical research. With expertise acquired in almost two decades
of<a href="drugex.htm"> experience</a> we can help you navigate
the challenges of multinational drug development.</p>
<p>Corning Besselaar draws upon its comprehensive in-house
database of over 8,000 investigators, representing virtually
every medical speciality, that allows us to place studies quickly
with some of the worlds most experienced investigators.</p>
<p>To date, Corning Besselaar has managed more than 490
multicenter phase II - III trials involving more than 98,000
patients in the US, Australia and Europe.</p>
<p><strong><u>NATIONAL PHASE III STUDIES</u></strong></p>
<p>Studies in single countries offer a range of benefits
including lower cost, ease of communication, homogeneity of
patient populations, diagnoses and treatments.At Corning
Besselaar Europe, we offer extensive experience in conducting
large and small projects at the national level. We provide a
range of specific services to complement your own resources.</p>
<p><strong>Where You Need Us</strong></p>
<p>Our local presence has allowed us to develop close
relationships with national authorities and a large number of
investigators. Corning Besselaar performs studies throughout
Europe from offices in Belgium, United Kingdom, Germany, France,
Switzerland, Sweden and Ireland. Monitors typically handle all
study activities in the local language, but we prepare study
documentation and reports in the language of your choice.</p>
<p><strong>Choose The Services You Need</strong></p>
<p>From <a href="ddc.htm">drug development </a>planning to expert
reports, the full spectrum of Corning Besselaar and<a
href="cps.htm"> Corning Pharmaceutical Services</a> is at your
command, either individually or as a package. Among our
specialities you will find feasibility studies, protocol/report
writing and monitoring-only programmes.</p>
<p><strong><u>MULTINATIONAL PHASE III STUDIES</u></strong></p>
<p>Tightly controlled multinational studies offer the most
cost-effective way of getting your drug to market. Our wide
access to investigators and patients allows for faster
recruitment of the large populations required in today's <a
href="regulato.htm">regulatory</a> environment.</p>
<p>During Corning Besselaar Europe's decade of <a
href="drugex.htm">experience</a> we have streamlined our
procedures, making execution of tasks faster and more accurate
from study design to final report. People and systems, including
clinical trial supplies handling, are in place to conduct your
multinational trials, increasing your strategic options for drug
development.</p>
<p>Multilingual staff in eight strategically placed offices
assist you with pan-European programmes.</p>
<p>When you choose Corning Besselaar, we become a part of your
team, employing communications technology such as
videoconferencing and electronic mail to keep you constantly
informed. A dedicated project manager and team members in
different countries perform your study to a single, high quality
standard.</p>
<p><a href="edmc.htm">Data Management</a> Facilities.</p>
<p>Qualified professional data management personnel are part of
the Corning Besselaar study team and work hand in hand with
Corning Besselaar clinical research staff throughout Europe to
process and analyse data from studies quickly and efficiently
using the facilities of the<a href="edmc.htm"> European Data
Management Centre</a> (EDMC)</p>
<hr>
<p align="center"><MAP NAME="FrontPageMap1"><AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="366, 6, 453, 106" HREF="library.htm"><AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="278, 7, 363, 103" HREF="cps.htm"><AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="187, 7, 272, 103" HREF="caropps.htm"><AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="97, 7, 182, 103" HREF="contact.htm"><AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="6, 7, 92, 103" HREF="index.htm"><AREA COORDS="0,0,10000,10000" HREF="index.htm"></MAP><a href="/corningb/_vti_map/phaseiii.htm.1.map"><img
