<head>
<title>Corning Hazleton - Preclinical Centre</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
<meta name="FORMATTER" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>
<body background="images/backgrnd.gif">
<p align="center"><MAP NAME="FrontPageMap"><AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="4, 3, 103, 37" HREF="index.htm"></MAP><a href="/corningb/_vti_map/hazel.htm.map"><img
align="bottom" src="images/home.gif" width="104" alt="Home Page"
ismap usemap="#FrontPageMap" height="38" border="0"></a></p>
<p align="center"><img src="images/hazelbg2.gif" align="bottom"
width="360" height="30"></p>
<p>Corning Hazleton is internationally recognized as a leader in
life sciences research, with nearly half a century of experience
in toxicology testing, chemistry support services and product
release testing.</p>
<p>Corning Hazleton in Leeds, as part of Corning Pharmaceutical
Services offers a world of preclinical and analytical
capabilities from Washington DC and Wisconsin in the USA, to
Harrogate in the UK.</p>
<h3>Safety Assessment Services</h3>
<p>Corning Hazleton offers experienced data managers and
scientifically sound, cost effective studies for the rapid safety
assessment of new products.</p>
<p>We offer analytical and immunoassay development/validation and
simple analysis in addition to quality control testing of
biotechnology products.We are uniquely qualified to provide
consulting advice in the development of preclinical programs for
all pharmaceutical and biotechnology projects.</p>
<h3>Analytical and Metabolism Services</h3>
<p>Our scientists are dedicated to meeting the most exact
preclinical and clinical standards. Unparalleled in our novel
approach to assisting fast track compound development, we have
invested the latest API LC-MS-MS analytical technology,
technology that has redefined the expectations of Bioanalysis. In
vitro studies have a large part to play in our approach to
compound development. Our laboratories in the US and Europe
continually offer new services to aid in compound appraisal and
development, in addition to classical metabolism studies.</p>
<p>&#160; </p>
