<html>
<head>
<title>Health Economics</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
<meta name="FORMATTER" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>
<body background="images/backgrnd.gif">
<h1 align="center"><MAP NAME="FrontPageMap"><AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="2, 4, 103, 37" HREF="index.htm"></MAP><a href="/corningb/_vti_map/health.htm.map"><img
align="bottom" src="images/home.gif" width="104" alt="Home Page"
ismap usemap="#FrontPageMap" height="38" border="0"></a></h1>
<h1 align="center"><img src="images/logo.gif" align="bottom"
width="363" height="31"></h1>
<h1><u>Health Economics at Corning Besselaar</u></h1>
<p>Health Economics is the study of choice in healthcare. It aims
to look at how decision makers such as doctors, purchasers of
healthcare services and patients make their choice from the
bewildering way of products and services that are associated with
healthcare under conditions of limited resources.</p>
<p>The increasing demographic pressure of the ageing population
and rising cost of technology are placing an increased emphasis
on health economics in assisting the rational use of healthcare
resources. This effect spills over into the pharmaceutical
industry where companies find themselves being increasingly
pressurised to provide health economic information for drugs and
products that they are introducing or establishing within the
pharmaceutical market place.</p>
<p>This trend is recognised within Corning Besselaar where there
is a commitment to providing high quality, timely, and
appropriate health economic studies, Corning Besselaar, together
with its sister companies, <a
href="http://www.bio.com/home/corning/companies.html">Corning HTA</a>
and <a href="pact.htm">Corning PACT</a> are able to provide the
full range of pharmaceutical economic services. These include:</p>
<h2><a href="phasei.htm"><u>Phase I</u></a></h2>
<p>The application of market assessments and epidemiological
tools to determine the strategic direction of drug programmes.</p>
<h2><a href="phaseii.htm"><u>Phase II</u></a></h2>
<p>The development of complex disease models to use as a basis
for the planning of Phase III and larger population studies.</p>
<h2><a href="edmc.htm"><u>Phase III</u></a></h2>
<p>The execution of health economic studies in parallel with the
Phase III development programme either incorporated within
traditional Phase Ill trials or as standalone health economic
studies.</p>
<h2><a href="pact.htm"><u>Phase IV</u></a></h2>
<p>The continuation of health economic studies into the real
world and naturalistic environment.</p>
<p>Corning Besselaar's strategy in providing health economics
studies, is to allow the pharmaceutical customers to purchase a
package of developments such that the introduction of
pharmacoeconomic and health economic studies can be controlled
and structured within the strategy of the development of
pharmaceutical compounds in today's changing environment.</p>
<p>Services offered by<a href="intro.htm"> Corning Besselaar</a>
are also sensitive to the current political pressures for cost
containment and a growing demand in society for a more
appropriate health care and the interests of the public in
improving the quality and opportunity for choice in healthcare
services. The experience and size of Coming Besselaar allows us
to deliver a high level of service at the stage of interaction
with the investigator site and the regulatory authorities.</p>
<p>This integrated range of services also extends beyond clinical
development into the communication of health economic health
studies within a wider audience. Therefore we are available to
conduct training seminars and exercises with field based
representatives and management staff, have the ability to produce
a wide range of papers and materials and can act as facilitators
with groups of diverse individuals for the description of the
factors important in the development of new compounds, e.g.
enlisting public perception.</p>
<p>The links with <a href="pact.htm">Coming PACT</a> and <a
href="http://www.bio.com/home/corning/companies.html">Corning HTA </a>provide
the services of Coming Besselaar with an instant access to over
twenty years of experience in health economics across the world.
In addition our European staff based in Maidenhead and Brussels
provide a range of experience with European decision-makers such
as the Transparency Commission in France and the District Health
Authorities in the UK. When linking this experience to our <a
href="regulato.htm">regulatory</a> colleagues, a powerful
grouping is formed which enables the speedy and appropriate
communication of health economics data to decision makers and
regulators.</p>
<p>In addition, the European group is very active in the
publications and education field. The recent publication of <strong>Health
Economics for the Uninitiated</strong> by Tony Lockett, one of
the team members within Corning Besselaar Health Economics is
more than testimony to this.</p>
<p><img src="images/lockett.gif" align="bottom" width="200"
height="320"></p>
<p>For further information on the range of services, please
contact ... </p>
<dl>
    <dd>Dr Tony Lockett</dd>
    <dd>Corning Besselaar Limited</dd>
    <dd>7 Roxborough Way</dd>
    <dd>Maidenhead SL6 3UD</dd>
    <dd>United Kingdom</dd>
</dl>
<p>Tel +44 (0) 1628 548000</p>
<p>Fax +44 (0) 1628 824508</p>
