Clearly, Congress must immediately put a stop using the thoroughly discredited
static &quot;tax expenditure&quot; method for estimation tax revenues from
tax-deferred plans such as IRAs.  The static method directs governmental tax policy
180 degrees in th e wrong direction.  Without changing any other provision of the
law, correctly measuring the tax impact of unlimited, tax-deductible IRAs would
swiftly increase the after-tax income of middle America by 12% to 20%! 
<p>

On November 8th, the American people voted for rational, substantive change, not
just slogans.  There's no sounder change than H.R. 3179 and S. 929 (103rd
Congress).  These identical bills achieve the desired results portrayed above and
will be reintroduc ed in the 104th Congress. 
<p>

Every caring American should write his or her Representative and Senators now and
urge immediate enactment.  There is no reason for delay.  Every day of delay makes
matters worse. 
<P>
