<li><a href="/abic/sentest.html.cgi">Testimony of Cleta Deatherage Mitchell</a> before the U.S. Senate<p>

<li>Check out what <a href="/abic/rogers.html.cgi">Will Rogers</a> had to say about the 1920,
 1924 and 1928 national political conventions. (You'll find that the more things change, the more they stay
the same...)<br><br>

<li>Also, read ABIC Director Cleta Mitchell's most recent analysis of the parties'
 positions on term limits in <a href="/abic/gopwoman.html.cgi">Term Limits: A Test
of Representation in Washington</a>
<br><br>

<li>Discover ABIC Director Cleta Mitchell's early, prophetic analysis of the Democrats' posit
ion on term limits in <a href="/abic/maindem.html.cgi">The Democratic Case for Term Limit
s</a><p>

<li>Get a quick read on the <a href="/abic/hstlvote.html.cgi">1995 House Term Limits vote</a>
 and the views of the <a href="/abic/peoplepie.html.cgi">American people</a> in charts 
prepared by ABIC.<br><br>

<li>Find out what's <a href="/abic/nextup.html.cgi">Next up on the Term Limits Agenda</a> in an article by <a href="/abic/cdmbio.html.cgi">Cleta Deatherage Mitchell</a><p> 

<li><a href="/abic/ptf/">Finger Pointing Page</a> and it
will do just that. We will name the names and point the fingers at
the members of Congress (or others) who do things we think you
should know about. We think you'd like to know who the scoundrels
and bad guys (and gals) in Washington really are and who may not
be identified as such by anyone else.<p>

<li>Read <a href="/abic/insider.html.cgi">Insider Tales of an Honorable Ex-Legislator</a> by <a href="/abic/cdmbio.html.cgi">Cleta Mitchell</a> for an insider's look into how even the most honorable lawmakers can become "players".<p>

<li>Why Did the Term Limits and Balanced Budget Amendments Fail in the 104th Congress?
<blockquote>
Read installment 1 of
<i><a href="/abic/book.html.cgi">Setting Limits: The 
Truth About Why
 Congress Defeated the Term Limits and Balanced Budget 
Amendments</a></i>
